contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:37.067 --> 00:39.000
 <I>( TOOL CLICKING )</I>

00:52.300 --> 00:54.501
Excuse Me, Sir?

00:54.501 --> 00:56.133
She's Not Coming.

00:56.133 --> 00:58.601
And I've Made
Everything Perfect.

00:58.601 --> 01:00.968
White Tea From China,

01:00.968 --> 01:04.167
Scottish Shortbread,
Devonshire Clotted Cream,

01:04.167 --> 01:06.534
And I Just Know
She's Not Coming.

01:06.534 --> 01:09.634
- Sir?
- <I>( CAR HONKS )</I>

01:09.634 --> 01:13.200
A Car, I Believe,
Is Approaching.

01:35.601 --> 01:36.834
Daisy.

01:36.834 --> 01:40.234
I've Waited
For This Moment
For So Long.

01:40.234 --> 01:42.300
 <I>I've Never Stopped</I>
 <I>Loving You,</I>

01:42.300 --> 01:44.601
Dreaming Of You.

01:44.601 --> 01:46.267
Woman:
 <I>I Know, Louis.</I>

01:47.834 --> 01:49.167
I Know.

01:51.534 --> 01:54.200
- ( GASPS )
- <I>( BELL RINGS )</I>

01:56.100 --> 01:57.701
Man ON Pa:
 <I>The Pep RALLY</I>

01:57.701 --> 01:59.834
 <I>HAS BEEN RELOCATED</I>
 <I>TO THE LITTLE GYM.</I>

02:08.501 --> 02:10.967
 <I>( GIRL CHUCKLES )</I>

02:10.967 --> 02:12.767
But Why Did
Fitzgerald

02:12.767 --> 02:14.467
Make Nick Carraway
So Dull?

02:14.467 --> 02:17.367
What's The Point Of Having
Such A Boring Narrator?

02:17.367 --> 02:19.501
I Think It Was
A Bad Choice.

02:19.501 --> 02:22.934
Well, Carraway Is
Like A Camera.

02:22.934 --> 02:25.667
He's Fascinated
By Gatsby,

02:25.667 --> 02:28.300
So He Wants To Create
A Portrait Of Him.

02:28.300 --> 02:30.601
Look, In A Way,
The Book Is Kind

02:30.601 --> 02:32.834
Of A Love Letter
To Gatsby.

02:32.834 --> 02:34.701
- Love Letter?
- Sure.

02:34.701 --> 02:36.968
- I Guess.
- Oh, I-- Oh!

02:36.968 --> 02:39.200
 <I>Excuse--</I>

02:45.100 --> 02:46.934
 <I>I Have Some Business</I>

02:46.934 --> 02:49.501
To Attend To In
The Teacher's Lounge,

02:49.501 --> 02:51.868
So We Can Talk
About This Again

02:51.868 --> 02:53.367
 <I>Next Week Before Class.</I>

02:53.367 --> 02:54.334
Sure.

02:57.033 --> 02:58.734
Finally Some Real
Tennis Weather.

02:59.801 --> 03:01.501
Good Afternoon.

03:06.434 --> 03:08.200
Oh!

03:16.767 --> 03:18.801
Narrator:
 <I>A Gentleman And His Impulses</I>

03:18.801 --> 03:21.868
 <I>Must Live In Constant</I>
 <I>Negotiation.</I>

03:23.567 --> 03:25.601
 <I>Louis Ives Had</I>
 <I>Been Determined</I>

03:25.601 --> 03:28.901
 <I>To Continue His Day</I>
 <I>With Dignity And Purpose.</I>

03:28.901 --> 03:31.033
 <I>But That Goal</I>

03:31.033 --> 03:33.667
 <I>Now Seemed</I>
 <I>Far Beyond His Reach.</I>

03:39.334 --> 03:40.901
( GASPING )
Oh!

03:42.367 --> 03:43.901
It Was
In Miss Jeffries' Bag.

03:48.334 --> 03:50.300
I'm Sure You're Aware
Princeton North Prep

03:50.300 --> 03:52.334
Did Not Meet Its
Funding Goals This Year.

03:52.334 --> 03:54.667
 <I>As A Result,</I>
 <I>We're Forced</I>
 <I>To Make Cutbacks.</I>

03:54.667 --> 03:55.868
I Understand.

03:55.868 --> 03:58.434
You Have Been An Excellent
Teacher, However.

03:58.434 --> 04:01.267
In Light Of This,
We Have Decided

04:01.267 --> 04:03.000
We're Willing
To Recommend You

04:03.000 --> 04:04.300
For Positions Elsewhere.

04:04.300 --> 04:06.200
Thank You.

04:07.934 --> 04:10.033
Actually,
For Some Time Now

04:10.033 --> 04:11.934
I've Considered Moving
To Manhattan.

04:11.934 --> 04:15.033
 <I>It's Always Been My Dream</I>
 <I>To Make A Living As A Writer.</I>

04:15.033 --> 04:18.000
Perhaps Now Would
Be A Good Time

04:18.000 --> 04:19.901
For A Big Change
Like That.

04:19.901 --> 04:21.767
Yes, Louis.
I Think Manhattan

04:21.767 --> 04:23.734
Sounds Like
A Very Fitting Place

04:23.734 --> 04:26.734
For A Young Man...
Like Yourself.

04:30.567 --> 04:32.901
Narrator:
 <I>But After His</I>
 <I>Crushing Dismissal,</I>

04:32.901 --> 04:37.167
 <I>Louis Ives Had No Courage</I>
 <I>For Such Bold Moves.</I>

04:37.167 --> 04:40.701
 <I>For The Brassiere Incident</I>
 <I>Had Crippled Him.</I>

04:40.701 --> 04:44.367
- <I>He Struggled To Deny</I>
 <I> These Strange Urges...</I>
- <I>( HORN HONKS )</I>

04:44.367 --> 04:46.734
 <I>...But In Moments Of Weakness</I>

04:46.734 --> 04:50.200
 <I>They Demanded Attention.</I>

04:50.200 --> 04:53.000
 <I>And So He Spent</I>
 <I>An Entire Summer</I>

04:53.000 --> 04:55.467
 <I>Immersed</I>
 <I>In The Solitary Routines</I>

04:55.467 --> 04:56.901
 <I>Of A Young Gentleman.</I>

04:56.901 --> 05:00.067
 <I>He Wore These Rituals</I>
 <I>Like Armor</I>

05:00.067 --> 05:02.634
 <I>To Shield Him</I>
 <I>From Despair.</I>

05:02.634 --> 05:06.367
 <I>But In Louis Ives'</I>
 <I>Darkest Moments,</I>

05:06.367 --> 05:08.968
 <I>He Feared</I>
 <I>He Was Unlovable.</I>

05:11.868 --> 05:13.734
 <I>It Was The Changing</I>
 <I>Of Leaves</I>

05:13.734 --> 05:16.367
 <I>That Finally Brought</I>
 <I>A Change In Perspective.</I>

05:16.367 --> 05:17.868
 <I>For Fall,</I>

05:17.868 --> 05:20.634
 <I>With Its Brisk Air</I>
 <I>And Clarity Of Light,</I>

05:20.634 --> 05:23.901
 <I>Rekindled The Feeling</I>
 <I>Of Possibility.</I>

05:37.567 --> 05:39.367
 <I>( PHONE RINGING )</I>

05:40.667 --> 05:42.501
Man ON PHONE:
 <I>H. Harrison. </I>

05:42.501 --> 05:44.601
- Hello.
- <I>Yes?</I>

05:44.601 --> 05:48.400
Yes, I'm Calling
About The Room? 
My Name Is--

05:48.400 --> 05:51.634
 <I>232 East 91ST.</I>

05:51.634 --> 05:54.467
- <I>Apartment 2f.</I>
- <I>( PHONE CLICKS )</I>

05:59.033 --> 06:00.033
2f.

06:00.033 --> 06:02.467
2f, 2f, 2f.

06:07.934 --> 06:09.267
 <I>( BUZZES )</I>

06:15.033 --> 06:17.133
- Man: <I>Are YOU</I>
 <I> THE APPLICANT?</I>
- Yes!

06:17.133 --> 06:19.267
 <I>Yes, It's Me.</I>

06:19.267 --> 06:21.133
( DOOR BUZZES )

06:34.200 --> 06:36.000
Harrison, Henry.

06:36.000 --> 06:37.701
Henry Harrison.

06:37.701 --> 06:38.701
Ives, Louis.

06:38.701 --> 06:40.033
Louis Ives.

06:41.100 --> 06:43.133
Kitchen. Bath.

06:43.133 --> 06:45.000
( CLEARS THROAT )
There's A Missing Door,

06:45.000 --> 06:46.834
But These Provide
Adequate Privacy.

06:46.834 --> 06:49.334
- Whoops.
- As You See.

06:49.334 --> 06:50.801
These Would Be
Your Chambers.

06:50.801 --> 06:53.467
It's Barracks-Style Living,
To Be Sure.

06:55.133 --> 06:57.400
You Can Certainly
Hear The Pigeons.

06:57.400 --> 07:00.501
Yes, I Like To Have
Access To Nature,
Don't You?

07:00.501 --> 07:02.033
 <I>If You Need</I>
 <I>More Drawer Space,</I>

07:02.033 --> 07:05.067
I Have Some
Empty File Cabinets
In The Kitchen.

07:05.067 --> 07:06.501
Okay.

07:06.501 --> 07:09.334
So There Are A Few Things
I'd Need To Know About You,

07:09.334 --> 07:10.634
If You Haven't
Lost Interest.

07:10.634 --> 07:13.400
Would You Prefer
To Leave Or Continue?

07:17.601 --> 07:19.067
Name?

07:20.234 --> 07:21.934
Louis Ives.

07:25.334 --> 07:28.067
Those Christmas Balls
Are Very Interesting.

07:28.067 --> 07:30.033
I Love Them.

07:30.033 --> 07:31.467
 <I>I Love Their Colors,</I>

07:31.467 --> 07:33.434
The Way They Catch
The Light.

07:33.434 --> 07:35.701
If You Ever Want
To Give Me Something,

07:35.701 --> 07:37.968
You Can Give Me
Christmas Balls.

07:37.968 --> 07:40.667
- Okay.
- So Tell Me...

07:40.667 --> 07:44.234
Louis Ives,
Why Are You Moving
To New York?

07:44.234 --> 07:45.634
( CLEARS THROAT )

07:45.634 --> 07:47.234
I'm Sort Of Looking
For Myself.

07:47.234 --> 07:49.033
You Won't Find Yourself
In New York.

07:49.033 --> 07:51.400
If I Had To Move Anywhere,
I'd Move To Russia.

07:51.400 --> 07:52.934
 <I>Far Less Expensive.</I>

07:52.934 --> 07:55.701
Well, I've Been Teaching
Now For Several Years,

07:55.701 --> 07:58.033
So As Far As The Rent
Is Concerned,

07:58.033 --> 07:59.267
I've Saved Enough

07:59.267 --> 08:00.334
From Working
In Princeton--

08:00.334 --> 08:01.667
Princeton?!

08:01.667 --> 08:04.167
How Is Princeton
These Days?

08:04.167 --> 08:07.367
It Was Great Once,
But Then They Let Women In.

08:07.367 --> 08:10.033
Oh, You Mean
The University.

08:10.033 --> 08:12.400
It's Still Excellent.

08:12.400 --> 08:14.901
And There's No Reason Women
Shouldn't Go To College.

08:14.901 --> 08:16.467
I'm Against
The Education Of Women.

08:17.667 --> 08:19.000
( LAUGHS )

08:19.000 --> 08:20.501
It Dulls Their Senses

08:20.501 --> 08:22.534
And Affects Their
Performance In The Boudoir.

08:22.534 --> 08:25.100
The Women I Like Best
Are The Hasidic Women.

08:25.100 --> 08:26.267
They Really Get It.

08:26.267 --> 08:29.467
 <I>What Were You Teaching?</I>

08:29.467 --> 08:30.868
English Literature.

08:30.868 --> 08:32.366
We're Colleagues Then.

08:32.366 --> 08:34.701
- I Teach Composition
At Queens College.
- Oh.

08:34.701 --> 08:36.366
Primarily,
I'm A Playwright.

08:36.366 --> 08:39.868
Really?
Have I Seen
Any Of Your Work?

08:39.868 --> 08:43.967
Sadly My Great Opus Was
Stolen By A Swiss Hunchback,

08:43.967 --> 08:46.200
But That's All Too Tragic
To Go Into Now.

08:46.200 --> 08:48.100
 <I>You Know, Fitzgerald Wrote</I>
 <I>With Great Love</I>

08:48.100 --> 08:51.434
About Princeton
In "This Side Of Paradise."

08:51.434 --> 08:53.801
Do You Like Fitzgerald?

08:53.801 --> 08:55.567
 <I>He's One Of My</I>
 <I>Favorite Authors.</I>

08:55.567 --> 08:57.200
Of Course I Like
Fitzgerald.

08:57.200 --> 08:59.267
 <I>But There Won't Be</I>
 <I>Anymore Of His Kind</I>

08:59.267 --> 09:00.300
 <I>Coming Along Soon.</I>

09:00.300 --> 09:02.367
You Need
An All-Male Environment

09:02.367 --> 09:04.234
To Shape Up
A Young Writer.

09:04.234 --> 09:06.934
The Muslims Might Produce
Another Fitzgerald.

09:06.934 --> 09:09.300
They're Very Good
At Separating The Sexes.

09:09.300 --> 09:11.601
On The Subject Of...
( CLEARS THROAT )

09:11.601 --> 09:13.734
 <I>The Sexes,</I>

09:13.734 --> 09:15.534
Just Out Of Curiosity,

09:15.534 --> 09:19.267
What Is Your Policy
Regarding Guests?

09:19.267 --> 09:22.834
As In...
Overnight Guests?

09:22.834 --> 09:25.167
- Uh...
- No.

09:25.167 --> 09:27.534
No, Absolutely Not.

09:27.534 --> 09:30.267
No. No, This Place
Is Far Too Small.

09:30.267 --> 09:32.400
There's To Be
No Fornication!

09:32.400 --> 09:35.434
No, I Wouldn't
Even Conceive

09:35.434 --> 09:38.067
Of Having Sex In Here.

09:38.067 --> 09:39.601
I'm Retired From All
That Anyway.

09:39.601 --> 09:41.734
I Didn't Mean To Be Rude,
I Was Just--

09:41.734 --> 09:43.267
This Has Gone On
Long Enough.

09:43.267 --> 09:45.667
We're Obviously Compatible.
You're The Only Person

09:45.667 --> 09:47.667
Who's Come For The Room
Who Speaks English.

09:47.667 --> 09:49.501
 <I>So What Will It Be,</I>
 <I>Yes Or No?</I>

09:49.501 --> 09:51.067
( GRUNTS SOFTLY )

09:51.067 --> 09:54.100
I Would Prefer
To Think About It.

09:56.734 --> 09:59.667
- <I>( CELL PHONE RINGING )</I>
- Waiter: Be Right Back.

10:03.400 --> 10:06.467
- Hello?
- So Have You
Thought About It?

10:06.467 --> 10:08.501
Oh, Hello.

10:08.501 --> 10:11.501
Yes. Actually,
I Just Was--

10:11.501 --> 10:12.667
And?

10:12.667 --> 10:15.501
Well...
( CLEARS THROAT )

10:15.501 --> 10:17.801
I'm Feeling...

10:17.801 --> 10:20.667
That I Should Wait Until
I'm Certain About A Job.

10:20.667 --> 10:22.100
No No.
No No No No.

10:22.100 --> 10:23.968
We Should Do This.
We Should Settle Now.

10:23.968 --> 10:26.467
 <I>You CAN PAY BY THE WEEK</I>
 <I>UNTIL YOU HAVE A JOB.</I>

10:26.467 --> 10:30.167
Plus There's Much I Can
Teach You About New York.

10:30.167 --> 10:32.000
I Can Advance You
Socially.

10:32.000 --> 10:34.000
All This Will Be
Very Good For You.

10:34.000 --> 10:37.934
That's Certainly
Very Considerate Of You
To Think That Way.

10:37.934 --> 10:39.334
Very Good, Then.
I'll See You

10:39.334 --> 10:41.801
On The First Of The Month.
I'm Glad This Worked Out.

10:45.367 --> 10:47.400
Narrator:
 <I>The Young Gentleman</I>
 <I>Was Troubled</I>

10:47.400 --> 10:49.767
 <I>That The Decision</I>
 <I>Was Made For Him.</I>

10:49.767 --> 10:51.968
 <I>Yet, It Had Been</I>
 <I>Some Time</I>

10:51.968 --> 10:54.033
 <I>Since He Felt</I>
 <I>This Wanted. </I>

10:54.033 --> 10:56.734
 <I>And As Strange</I>
 <I>As It All Seemed,</I>

10:56.734 --> 10:58.667
 <I>He Was</I>
 <I>Inexplicably Drawn</I>

10:58.667 --> 11:00.868
 <I>To This</I>
 <I>Mr. Henry Harrison.</I>

11:02.834 --> 11:05.167
 <I>( POP MUSIC PLAYING )</I>

11:22.100 --> 11:24.901
 <I>* Daylight Turns</I>
 <I>To Moonlight *</I>

11:24.901 --> 11:29.033
 <I>* And I'm At My Best *</I>

11:29.033 --> 11:32.167
 <I>* Praising The Way</I>
 <I>It All Works *</I>

11:32.167 --> 11:35.567
 <I>* And Gazing Upon</I>
 <I>The Rest, Yeah * </I>

11:35.567 --> 11:39.234
 <I>* The Cool Before The Warm,</I>
 <I>The Calm After The Storm * </I>

11:39.234 --> 11:42.901
 <I>* The Cool Before The Warm,</I>
 <I>The Calm After The Storm * </I>

11:42.901 --> 11:46.033
 <I>* I Wish To Stay</I>
 <I>Forever *</I>

11:46.033 --> 11:48.067
 <I>* Letting This Be</I>
 <I>My Food-- *</I>

11:48.067 --> 11:50.400
 <I>( TOILET FLUSHING )</I>

11:51.901 --> 11:54.968
- <I>( CLEARS THROAT )</I>
- <I>( FLATULATES )</I>

11:56.133 --> 11:58.734
- <I>( COUGHS )</I>
- <I>( GROANS )</I>

12:10.701 --> 12:12.334
Tell Me
Your Name Again.

12:12.334 --> 12:14.234
Louis.

12:14.234 --> 12:15.434
My Name's Louis.

12:15.434 --> 12:17.601
Don't Worry,
It Will Eventually Sink In.

12:17.601 --> 12:19.968
I'm Glad To See You've
Moved In So Nicely.

12:19.968 --> 12:23.234
I Apologize That Gershon
Couldn't Help Carry
Your Things.

12:23.234 --> 12:24.667
He's Not Speaking To Me.

12:24.667 --> 12:26.734
That's Fine.
Who's Gershon?

12:26.734 --> 12:28.601
He's A Friend
Who Helps Carry Things.

12:28.601 --> 12:30.133
And Fix My Car.

12:30.133 --> 12:33.200
Speaking Of Which,
I Was Admiring Yours Earlier.
What Make Is That?

12:33.200 --> 12:36.734
Oh, It's
A Pontiac Grand Ville.

12:36.734 --> 12:38.734
It Was My Father's.

12:38.734 --> 12:39.934
In A Weird Way,

12:39.934 --> 12:42.367
It's Sort Of All
I Have Left Of Him.

12:42.367 --> 12:45.067
He Died My Freshman Year
Of College.

12:45.067 --> 12:49.434
My Mother Passed
Only A Few Years After.

12:49.434 --> 12:52.100
Well...

12:52.100 --> 12:53.267
I Drive A Buick.

12:53.267 --> 12:56.167
- Hmm.
- What Are You
Reading There?

12:56.167 --> 12:57.400
Henry James.

12:57.400 --> 12:59.033
He's Unreadable.

12:59.033 --> 13:00.868
 <I>His Early Work</I>
 <I>Wasn't As Bad.</I>

13:00.868 --> 13:02.434
He Burned Himself,
You Know?

13:02.434 --> 13:05.334
He Sat On A Stove
And Shriveled His Testicles.

13:05.334 --> 13:09.400
That May Account
For His Sudden Change
Of Style.

13:09.400 --> 13:11.200
I Didn't Know That.

13:11.200 --> 13:13.334
Yes. Well, You'd Better
Get Some Rest.

13:13.334 --> 13:14.634
I Imagine You're
Still Growing.

13:22.400 --> 13:24.133
 <I>( LOUD CLASSICAL MUSIC</I>
 <I>PLAYING )</I>

13:24.133 --> 13:25.834
 <I>( Henry GRUNTING )</I>

13:28.834 --> 13:30.734
Henry:
 <I>Yeah! </I>

13:33.234 --> 13:35.234
 <I>( GRUNTING CONTINUING )</I>

13:43.033 --> 13:45.200
Ahhh.
Ow.

13:49.334 --> 13:51.033
Ahh!

13:51.033 --> 13:53.667
Go! No!
Go Back!

13:53.667 --> 13:54.868
- <I>Back To Your Room.</I>
- No--

13:54.868 --> 13:56.868
I Don't Like You Lurking
There In The Shadows.

13:56.868 --> 13:59.767
I'm Sorry, Henry!
I Just Didn't Know 
What Was Happening.

13:59.767 --> 14:02.434
I Can't Be Seen
When I'm Dancing!

14:02.434 --> 14:04.267
 <I>I Forgot You Were Here.</I>

14:04.267 --> 14:07.234
 <I>Next Time I Exercise,</I>
 <I>I'll Make Sure That You're Out.</I>

14:07.234 --> 14:09.701
But Sometimes
The Need Is Too Great!

14:09.701 --> 14:12.834
- No Problem.
- One Must Keep In Shape,
You Know?

14:12.834 --> 14:16.868
I Try To Move Whatever
I Think Is Rotting.

14:22.934 --> 14:24.634
I Tell You, Louis,

14:24.634 --> 14:26.367
I'd Like To Hire You.

14:26.367 --> 14:29.434
For Now It's Gonna Be
Mostly Be Phone Sales

14:29.434 --> 14:31.467
 <I>To Businesses</I>
 <I>And To Museums.</I>

14:31.467 --> 14:33.901
But It Does Go
Without Saying--

14:33.901 --> 14:35.868
This Being
An Environmental
Journal--

14:35.868 --> 14:37.167
You Are Green?

14:37.167 --> 14:40.033
 <I>You Do Live</I>
 <I>A Pro-Environmental</I>
 <I>Lifestyle?</I>

14:40.033 --> 14:41.033
 <I>Yes.</I>

14:41.033 --> 14:43.634
- Yes, Of Course.
- Good.

14:43.634 --> 14:46.601
I'm Very Environmental.

14:46.601 --> 14:48.734
I'm Always Thinking

14:48.734 --> 14:51.767
About How The World
Is Falling Apart.

14:51.767 --> 14:55.534
And Then
I Get Depressed

14:55.534 --> 14:57.167
And I Think About--

14:57.167 --> 14:59.334
Well, If I Think
About Myself

14:59.334 --> 15:00.467
 <I>That's Also Depressing.</I>

15:00.467 --> 15:01.767
- Good.
- <I>( KNOCKING ON DOOR )</I>

15:03.200 --> 15:05.701
- Yeah?
- Sorry To Interrupt,
George,

15:05.701 --> 15:08.467
But I Need You To Look
At These Right Away

15:08.467 --> 15:10.334
So I Can Get
Them Scanned.

15:10.334 --> 15:11.267
Okay.

15:13.968 --> 15:15.701
 <I>Oh, She's Got</I>
 <I>Nice Feathers.</I>

15:16.834 --> 15:19.267
But I Like Her Eyes.
This Is The One.

15:19.267 --> 15:21.367
- Great.
- <I>I Agree.</I>

15:21.367 --> 15:23.434
That's An Excellent
Owl Photo.

15:23.434 --> 15:26.167
