Your Getting A Job.

17:31.701 --> 17:32.901
Tomorrow Evening.

17:32.901 --> 17:34.567
I'll Take You
To The Opera.

17:34.567 --> 17:36.701
I Know A Wonderful
Little Company.

17:36.701 --> 17:38.167
My Treat.

17:38.167 --> 17:40.467
Thank You, Herbert.
Good Night.

17:40.467 --> 17:43.100
Good Night.

17:54.501 --> 17:55.667
- This Way.
- Woman: <I>Excuse Me.</I>

17:55.667 --> 17:58.300
Excuse Me, I Had
My Eye On That First.

17:58.300 --> 18:00.901
The Doorman Was Watching
This Pile For Me.

18:00.901 --> 18:04.100
Henry:
Bloody Hell, I Forgot It
Was Trash Day.

18:04.100 --> 18:05.367
Oh, Well.

18:05.367 --> 18:07.734
Are You Sure About Going
To The Opera Tonight?

18:07.734 --> 18:09.901
I Hear It's
Astronomically Expensive.

18:09.901 --> 18:12.834
Don't-- Don't Be
So Middle-Class.

18:12.834 --> 18:15.934
The Aristocracy
Never Pays.

18:15.934 --> 18:17.934
 <I>Here's My Car.</I>

18:19.634 --> 18:22.234
( HUMMING )

18:23.968 --> 18:26.968
- Maybe We Should
Take A Cab?
- Why?

18:28.067 --> 18:29.801
I Go Everywhere
In My Electra.

18:29.801 --> 18:31.300
I Drive All
Around Manhattan

18:31.300 --> 18:32.634
Looking For "It."

18:32.634 --> 18:35.434
I Mean "It"
In The Kerouac Sense.

18:35.434 --> 18:37.033
Why Do You Have
Florida Plates?

18:37.033 --> 18:38.534
Because I Live There
Part-Time--

18:38.534 --> 18:40.534
Palm Beach.

18:40.534 --> 18:42.501
 <I>That's Where</I>
 <I>The Social Life Goes</I>
 <I>In The Winter.</I>

18:45.167 --> 18:47.467
I Can Only Afford
One Working Door.

18:47.467 --> 18:50.501
Just Close It
Tightly Behind You.

18:50.501 --> 18:52.334
( SINGING )

18:52.334 --> 18:53.834
Henry, Henry, Henry!

18:53.834 --> 18:55.334
- Please, Be Careful!
- Ohh!

18:55.334 --> 18:57.701
You Don't Even Have
