You're Later Than Usual.

30:32.501 --> 30:35.467
What?! Yes.
I Went Out For Drinks.

30:37.868 --> 30:40.601
Actually, I'm Sort Of Seeing
This Girl From Work.

30:40.601 --> 30:43.267
Oh, That Sounds
Like A Lie.

30:43.267 --> 30:44.601
But That's Good.

30:44.601 --> 30:46.200
 <I>That Shows That</I>
 <I>You're Growing Up.</I>

30:46.200 --> 30:48.367
 <I>By The Way,</I>
 <I>Have You Seen</I>
 <I>My Eye Mask?</I>

30:48.367 --> 30:50.300
It's Disappeared
Mysteriously.

30:50.300 --> 30:52.133
- No.
- <I>I Certainly Hope</I>
 <I> It Turns Up.</I>

30:52.133 --> 30:53.767
I Can't Sleep
Without It.

30:53.767 --> 30:57.868
By The Way,
I Got The Mail On My Way Up.

30:57.868 --> 31:00.334
Ohh...

31:00.334 --> 31:03.467
Oh, Speaking Of Which,
I Forgot To Mention This--

31:03.467 --> 31:05.868
Never Answer The Door.
It Could Be The Irs.

31:05.868 --> 31:09.868
Okay.
Who's Otto Bellman?

31:09.868 --> 31:11.033
Who, Bellman?

31:11.033 --> 31:12.734
He Was Your Predecessor.

31:13.801 --> 31:16.701
Oh. How Long Did
He Live Here?

31:16.701 --> 31:19.033
Two Years.
It Was A Great Mistake.

31:19.033 --> 31:20.868
At First It Wasn't Awful.

31:20.868 --> 31:23.968
He Looked Like
Sophia Loren In Profile.

31:23.968 --> 31:27.367
Of Course...
He Had A Hunchback.

31:28.934 --> 31:30.968
You're Putting The Mail
In The Freezer?

31:30.968 --> 31:33.200
Only His Letters.
I Can't Afford To Lose Them.

31:33.200 --> 31:36.934
He's Already Hell-Bent
On Revenge Against Me.

31:36.934 --> 31:38.334
Why?

31:38.334 --> 31:41.400
- Because I Kicked Him Out.
- Really?

31:41.400 --> 31:43.434
For Being
A Sexual Deviant.

31:43.434 --> 31:44.834
Oh.

31:44.834 --> 31:49.133
He Had One Of Those
Bondage Magazines.

31:50.367 --> 31:54.167
He's Swiss--
They Like All That S&M,

31:54.167 --> 31:55.200
You Know?

31:56.934 --> 31:59.133
Can You Believe
He's Actually Living

31:59.133 --> 32:01.601
With Vivian Cudlip's
Granddaughter?

32:01.601 --> 32:03.400
And What Is Worse,

32:03.400 --> 32:07.100
He Stole The Only Copy
Of My Greatest Play.

32:07.100 --> 32:10.567
"Henry And Mary
Are Always Late."

32:10.567 --> 32:12.968
 <I>The Degenerate Is Probably</I>
 <I>Gonna Have It Produced</I>

32:12.968 --> 32:14.501
 <I>Illegally In Zurich</I>

32:14.501 --> 32:16.534
And Make Himself
A Grand Fortune.

32:16.534 --> 32:18.200
I Think You're Being
Unreasonable.

32:18.200 --> 32:21.801
You're The One Always
Citing These Great Authors.

32:21.801 --> 32:24.300
Most Of Them Had All Kinds
Of Unusual Kinks.

32:24.300 --> 32:27.334
That's Irrelevant.
One Should Only Have Sex
When Married.

32:27.334 --> 32:28.868
Have You
Ever Been Married?

32:28.868 --> 32:30.467
No.

32:30.467 --> 32:33.968
Are You Saying
You've Never Had Sex?

32:33.968 --> 32:37.968
You'll Get
Nothing Out Of Me.

32:37.968 --> 32:40.601
 <I>And Try Thinking</I>
 <I>About More Important Things.</I>

32:40.601 --> 32:43.567
Think About Defrosting
That Icebox In There

32:43.567 --> 32:45.334
To Make Room
For More Mail.

32:45.334 --> 32:48.501
 <I>That's What I Do.</I>
 <I>I Don't Go Around Needing Sex.</I>

32:48.501 --> 32:50.133
I Don't Need Any Love.

32:50.133 --> 32:53.267
You're Being Dishonest.
Everybody Needs Something.

32:53.267 --> 32:55.234
All I Need Is Pleasure.

32:55.234 --> 32:57.934
Okay, So What
Gives You Pleasure?

33:00.868 --> 33:02.968
I'd Like To Go
Back To Anapa.

33:02.968 --> 33:05.501
 <I>It's A Small Town</I>

33:05.501 --> 33:07.601
On The Black Sea
In Russia.

33:09.934 --> 33:13.467
Vivian And I Went There
Years Ago On Our World Tour.

33:13.467 --> 33:17.300
 <I>A Bottle Of Champagne</I>
 <I>Only Cost $4.</I>

33:18.367 --> 33:20.167
In My Mind's Eye,

33:20.167 --> 33:23.067
That's Where I Think
I'd Be Happiest.

33:39.767 --> 33:42.467
Narrator:
 <I>Louis Ives Rose</I>
 <I>The Next Morning,</I>

33:42.467 --> 33:45.534
 <I>Motivated To Finally</I>
 <I>Start Writing.</I>

33:45.534 --> 33:49.868
 <I>( MAN SINGING )</I>
 <I>* Beautiful Dreamer </I>

33:49.868 --> 33:53.667
 <I>* Wake Unto Me... </I>

33:53.667 --> 33:56.334
Narrator:
 <I>But As The Day</I>
 <I>Progressed,</I>

33:56.334 --> 33:58.634
 <I>The Oddness Of Life</I>

33:58.634 --> 34:00.667
 <I>Once Again</I>
 <I>Distracted Him.</I>

34:02.501 --> 34:06.033
 <I>* Sounds</I>
 <I>Of The Rude World *</I>

34:06.033 --> 34:09.033
 <I>* Heard In The Day </I>

34:09.033 --> 34:12.701
 <I>* Lulled By The Moonlight </I>

34:12.701 --> 34:16.400
 <I>* Have All Passed Away. </I>

34:23.132 --> 34:25.567
Henry,
Do You Know That Man?

34:27.601 --> 34:29.067
Henry:
 <I>That's Gershon Gruen.</I>

34:29.067 --> 34:31.634
 <I>Oh, Your Friend</I>
 <I>Who Carries Things?</I>

34:31.634 --> 34:33.501
 <I>Yes, And Fixes My Car.</I>

34:33.501 --> 34:36.067
It's Obvious He's Still
Not Speaking To Me.

34:36.067 --> 34:37.900
He's Always
On That Bike.

34:37.900 --> 34:40.833
Yes, He's Cycling Away
His Sex Drive.

34:40.833 --> 34:44.434
Gershon Was A Slave
To His Libido.

34:44.434 --> 34:46.934
He Used To Bring Prostitutes
From The Bronx

34:46.934 --> 34:48.367
Into His Apartment,

34:48.367 --> 34:49.634
And They Would
Steal Things.

34:49.634 --> 34:51.900
He Couldn't Stop,
So He Turned To Me For Help.

34:51.900 --> 34:53.400
I Told Him To Develop
Other Interests,

34:53.400 --> 34:56.100
Like Reading The Dictionary
To Improve His Vocabulary

34:56.100 --> 34:57.501
And Bicycle Riding,

34:57.501 --> 34:59.734
Which So Far
Has Worked Wonders.

34:59.734 --> 35:02.100
Of Course, He's Still
An Obsessive Masturbator.

35:02.100 --> 35:04.968
If Your Advice Worked,

35:04.968 --> 35:07.167
Then Why Isn't
He Speaking To You?

35:07.167 --> 35:10.634
He Claims That I Don't
Really Want His Friendship,

35:10.634 --> 35:13.100
That I Am Only Using Him
For His Mechanic Skills.

35:13.100 --> 35:15.133
Also, I Think He Was Jealous
Of My Relationship

35:15.133 --> 35:17.734
With Your Predecessor
Otto Bellman.

35:17.734 --> 35:22.601
You Have A Strange Power
Over People, Henry.

35:22.601 --> 35:25.100
It's My Constant
Disapproval.

35:25.100 --> 35:27.367
Some Find It Fatherly.

35:27.367 --> 35:29.667
No! Enough!

35:30.834 --> 35:33.133
I Think It's Silly
You Made Us Sit

35:33.133 --> 35:34.934
At Separate Tables
Like This.

35:34.934 --> 35:37.234
Men Of Any Worth
Sit Across From Women.

35:37.234 --> 35:39.501
If You Ever Want
To Be An Extra Man,

35:39.501 --> 35:42.100
You Have Much To Learn
About Boy-Girl Propriety.

35:42.100 --> 35:45.434
Which Reminds Me, What Are
You Doing Tomorrow Evening?

35:45.434 --> 35:47.367
Nothing. Why?

35:47.367 --> 35:49.868
I Have Two Lady Friends
Who Need Escorting To An Event.

35:51.767 --> 35:53.534
Vivian Cudlip
And Her Niece?

35:53.534 --> 35:55.834
No, But Almost
As Important.

35:55.834 --> 35:59.133
Would This Officially
Make Me An Extra Man?

35:59.133 --> 36:02.133
Extra, Yes.
But Nowhere Near Essential.

36:02.133 --> 36:03.934
 <I>( French MUSIC PLAYING )</I>

36:12.133 --> 36:13.667
Henry, What Are
You Doing?

36:13.667 --> 36:15.801
I Forgot To Buy Socks.

36:15.801 --> 36:17.434
Mine Are All
Threadbare.

36:17.434 --> 36:20.467
Don't Worry,
No One Will Notice.

36:20.467 --> 36:24.000
Who Knows, Maybe It'll
Help Kill The Fleas.

36:25.067 --> 36:26.801
Fleas?

36:26.801 --> 36:28.567
Yes. Fleas.

36:28.567 --> 36:30.501
My Dermatologist
Confirmed I Have Them.

36:32.434 --> 36:33.701
Henry:
 <I>Now Listen Carefully--</I>

36:33.701 --> 36:35.367
One Of The Women

36:35.367 --> 36:37.167
We're Escorting
This Evening, Lois Huber,

36:37.167 --> 36:39.701
Has Given Me A Room
In Her Palm Beach Home

36:39.701 --> 36:41.000
 <I>For The Last</I>
 <I>Four Seasons.</I>

36:41.000 --> 36:42.100
- Okay.
- Unfortunately,

36:42.100 --> 36:44.400
I Said Something
That Offended Her,

36:44.400 --> 36:46.000
 <I>And We Had</I>
 <I>A Falling Out.</I>

36:46.000 --> 36:47.567
What Did You Say
That Offended Her?

36:47.567 --> 36:49.601
I Told Her That Her
Ass Is Big,

36:49.601 --> 36:52.901
That She's A Saddle-Back
And Possibly A Moral Imbecile.

36:52.901 --> 36:55.801
Henry, That Seems Like
A Lot To Recover From.

36:55.801 --> 36:57.801
That's Where
I'm Counting On You.

36:57.801 --> 37:01.667
I'm Hoping That Your Youth
Will Have A Positive
Effect On Her.

37:02.801 --> 37:05.934
The Other Woman,
Meredith Lagerfeld,

37:05.934 --> 37:09.334
Has Nothing
To Offer Socially.
She's Dirt Poor.

37:09.334 --> 37:12.300
In Fact, We Often Work
In Unison At Events.

37:12.300 --> 37:15.667
She's The One Who Alerted Me
That Lois May Be Ready
To Forgive Me.

37:15.667 --> 37:17.367
- <I>That Was Nice Of Her.</I>
- Not Really.

37:17.367 --> 37:19.334
Lagerfeld Uses Me
For Rides.

37:19.334 --> 37:21.367
She's Gotten Quite Enormous,
You See,

37:21.367 --> 37:23.033
And Has Trouble Getting
Around Town.

37:23.033 --> 37:25.701
 <I>Speak Of The Devil.</I>

37:25.701 --> 37:27.501
 <I>My God, Look At Her.</I>

37:27.501 --> 37:30.801
She Does Have Nice Hair.

37:30.801 --> 37:32.567
 <I>I Suppose We All</I>
 <I>Have Something,</I>

37:32.567 --> 37:34.334
 <I>Even Lagerfeld.</I>

37:36.100 --> 37:38.200
Henry, Focus.

37:38.200 --> 37:41.434
The George Gillies
Have Just Arrived.

37:41.434 --> 37:44.100
She's Hosting Quite A Large
Party On Thursday.

37:44.100 --> 37:46.334
I Think We Should Try
To Speak To Her.

37:46.334 --> 37:48.200
They're Friends
Of Vivian Cudlip's.

37:48.200 --> 37:50.501
Mention The Name Vivian Cudlip
And We'll Be In.

37:50.501 --> 37:52.100
Meanwhile,
Where The Hell Is Lois?

37:52.100 --> 37:55.567
Oh, Lois, For Heaven's Sake.
She's Over By The Klimt.

37:55.567 --> 37:58.767
Hmm. Excuse Us.
Louis.

37:58.767 --> 38:00.868
Oh, Terribly Sorry.

38:08.834 --> 38:13.133
- There's A Dwarf
In That Picture.
- It's A Child, Henry.

38:13.133 --> 38:14.467
Yes, Quite Right.

38:14.467 --> 38:16.634
Speaking Of Children,
I'd Like To Introduce You

38:16.634 --> 38:19.234
To My Young House Guest
Louis Ives.

38:19.234 --> 38:22.434
Louis Has Recently Come
To New York To Find Himself.

38:22.434 --> 38:25.400
Lois, Louis,
Louis, Lois.

38:25.400 --> 38:28.767
Rolls Off The Tongue Rather
Nicely, Doesn't It?

38:30.801 --> 38:32.467
I Need Some More Wine.

38:38.634 --> 38:40.534
I Rea--
( CLEARS THROAT )

38:41.601 --> 38:44.000
I Really Like
These Paintings.

38:44.000 --> 38:45.234
I Don't.

38:45.234 --> 38:48.801
It's Ridiculous How Nobody
Really Looks At Them.

38:52.367 --> 38:55.834
I Was Admiring
Your Outfit Before.

38:55.834 --> 38:57.934
It's Very Interesting.

38:57.934 --> 39:00.701
And A Good Color
For You Too.

39:00.701 --> 39:04.033
And How Old
Are You, Louis?

39:04.033 --> 39:06.200
Old Enough.

39:06.200 --> 39:09.400
Tell Me, Are You
By Chance From Russia?

39:09.400 --> 39:11.534
Me?
( CHUCKLES )

39:11.534 --> 39:13.868
God, No.
I'm As American
As They Come.

39:15.367 --> 39:16.901
Not To Me.

39:18.200 --> 39:21.834
What Exactly Do You Do
With Magazines, Louis?

39:21.834 --> 39:24.701
I Work On The Marketing
Side Of Things,

39:24.701 --> 39:27.267
But I'd Like
To Be An Editor

39:27.267 --> 39:28.901
Or Writer Someday.

39:28.901 --> 39:32.200
Ah. Henry's
An Excellent Writer.

39:32.200 --> 39:33.467
A Talented Playwright.

39:33.467 --> 39:35.834
But He Can Be
A Very Rude Man,
You Know.

39:35.834 --> 39:38.200
- Ah.
- Meredith: Hello, Lois.

39:38.200 --> 39:40.434
With The Exception
Of That Russian Bartendress,

39:40.434 --> 39:43.200
I've Never Experienced
A More Dreary Crowd.

39:43.200 --> 39:46.167
Stop Complaining, Henry.
It's Tiresome.

39:46.167 --> 39:49.834
Well, There Is Another
Opening At The Whitney,

39:49.834 --> 39:51.734
But It's Not Until 9:00.

39:51.734 --> 39:53.767
Then I'll Need
Dinner First.

39:53.767 --> 39:57.267
We'll Eat At My Place.
Meredith Will Ride Over With Me,

39:57.267 --> 39:59.434
Henry And Louis Can Go
Pick Up The Food.

39:59.434 --> 40:01.033
- <I>Come, Dear.</I>
- That's Awfully Nice, Lois.

40:03.968 --> 40:06.267
 <I>Things With Lois Are Worse</I>
 <I>Than I Had Imagined.</I>

40:06.267 --> 40:08.467
Your Youth
Has Failed Us

40:08.467 --> 40:10.167
And I'm Off My Game.

40:10.167 --> 40:14.133
I Haven't Been Sleeping Right
Since My Eye Mask Disappeared.

40:14.133 --> 40:17.834
 <I>We'll Have No Choice</I>
 <I>But To Implement Plan B</I>
 <I>Over Dinner.</I>

40:17.834 --> 40:19.567
Next.

40:19.567 --> 40:22.000
There's No Bathroom In Here
And I Have To Piss.

40:22.000 --> 40:24.901
If I'm Not Back In Time,
Get Two Roasted Chickens.

40:24.901 --> 40:27.334
Lois Has Millions
Of Dollars,

40:27.334 --> 40:30.400
But There's Nothing
She Likes Better Than
Roasted Chicken.

40:32.634 --> 40:35.567
Narrator:
 <I>As The Young Gentleman</I>
 <I>Stood There On Line,</I>

40:35.567 --> 40:38.734
 <I>He Couldn't Help But Play</I>
 <I>The First Half Of The Evening</I>

40:38.734 --> 40:41.000
 <I>Over And Over</I>
 <I>In His Mind. </I>

40:41.000 --> 40:42.667
 <I>In Doing So,</I>

40:42.667 --> 40:44.734
 <I>Something Became</I>
 <I>Very Clear</I>

40:44.734 --> 40:47.067
 <I>About The Nature</I>
 <I>Of His Relationship</I>

40:47.067 --> 40:49.467
 <I>With Mr. Henry Harrison,</I>
 <I>Who--</I>

40:49.467 --> 40:50.968
- I'm Back.
- Oh.

40:50.968 --> 40:53.434
Did You Pee Already?

40:53.434 --> 40:55.501
- Yes.
- Where?

40:55.501 --> 40:57.400
Out There.

40:57.400 --> 40:58.934
Out In The Street?

40:58.934 --> 41:01.267
- Yes.
- No, You Didn't.

41:01.267 --> 41:03.767
Yes, I Did, Louis.

41:03.767 --> 41:07.434
A True Aristocrat Knows
That He Can Piss In The Street

41:07.434 --> 41:10.334
At Any Time He Wishes
Day Or Night.

41:10.334 --> 41:11.667
 <I>Next.</I>

41:11.667 --> 41:14.601
Henry, I Want To See
Where You Peed.

41:16.234 --> 41:17.567
Don't Be Ridiculous.

41:17.567 --> 41:19.100
Right There,
Between The Cars.

41:19.100 --> 41:22.300
How Did You Do It
Without Being Seen?

41:22.300 --> 41:23.834
You Could Have
Been Arrested.

41:25.534 --> 41:27.667
It's An Acquired Art.

41:27.667 --> 41:30.567
Look, I'll Show You.

41:31.968 --> 41:35.167
Now Watch,
And Do As I Do.

41:36.834 --> 41:38.534
Ready?

41:38.534 --> 41:41.834
Step Off The Curb
As If You're Going
To Walk Across The Street.

41:41.834 --> 41:43.868
Then You Stop Abruptly,

41:43.868 --> 41:45.267
Thinking Twice
About Crossing In Traffic.

41:45.267 --> 41:46.968
Meanwhile,
You've Undone
Your Zipper,

41:46.968 --> 41:48.367
You've Freed Yourself

41:48.367 --> 41:51.200
And Then,
Keeping A Wide Arc
With The Raincoat,

41:51.200 --> 41:53.300
You Step Backwards,
You See?

41:53.300 --> 41:56.601
This Way, No One Can
See You're Pissing,

41:56.601 --> 41:58.901
And The Walking
Backwards Part

41:58.901 --> 42:01.334
Keeps You From Pissing
On Your Legs,

42:01.334 --> 42:03.000
Not To Mention
Stepping In It.

42:04.701 --> 42:08.000
Oh, I Just Did
A Bit More.

42:09.334 --> 42:11.100
So Now Do You
Understand?

42:12.534 --> 42:16.200
I Think
I Actually Do. Yeah.

42:16.200 --> 42:18.267
Thank You
For Teaching Me That.

42:18.267 --> 42:20.467
You're Welcome.
And Keep The Change.

42:20.467 --> 42:22.501
 <I>Don't Mention It.</I>

42:22.501 --> 42:25.534
- Good Evening.
- Henry Harrison
For Mrs. Hueber.

42:25.534 --> 42:26.501
Of Course.

42:27.901 --> 42:29.434
Wow.

42:35.701 --> 42:37.167
Whatever You Do,

42:37.167 --> 42:40.033
Don't Mention
The Fleas To Lois.

42:40.033 --> 42:42.701
If She Catches Them,
She'll Know They're From Me.

42:42.701 --> 42:44.834
Then I'll Never
Get That Room.

42:44.834 --> 42:47.234
 <I>Ma'am,</I>
 <I>Mr. Harrison.</I>

42:47.234 --> 42:48.834
Wait. Wait.

42:48.834 --> 42:50.734
Lois Has A Dog.

42:50.734 --> 42:54.033
If I Can Transfer
My Fleas To Her Dog,

42:54.033 --> 42:55.834
- We'll Be Saved.
- <I>( ELEVATOR BELL RINGS )</I>

42:55.834 --> 42:56.801
Doorman:
 <I>Going Up?</I>

42:58.067 --> 42:59.834
- ( BARKING )
- <I>Lovie!</I>

42:59.834 --> 43:04.501
Oh, What A Good Girl.
Oh, I've Missed You!

43:04.501 --> 43:06.701
Look At You
With Your Little--

43:06.701 --> 43:08.567
What The Hell
Is That On You?

43:08.567 --> 43:10.801
Looks Like
An Elizabethan Collar.

43:10.801 --> 43:12.634
Henry, Put The Dog Down

43:12.634 --> 43:14.200
And Bring Me Those
Roasted Chickens.

43:14.200 --> 43:16.400
Right Away.
Right Away.

43:16.400 --> 43:17.868
- Put It Down, Henry!
- ( BARKS )

43:17.868 --> 43:19.501
I'm Coming.

43:21.634 --> 43:22.767
Oh.

43:27.367 --> 43:29.033
Hello, Meredith.

43:33.968 --> 43:35.501
Um...

43:38.734 --> 43:40.868
Wow.

43:40.868 --> 43:43.000
What An Amazing View.

43:43.000 --> 43:45.300
You Can See Everything
From Here.

43:45.300 --> 43:47.868
I Know. I Grew Up
In This Neighborhood.

43:49.467 --> 43:50.501
Did You Really?

43:52.200 --> 43:54.334
We Were The Most
Popular Family.

43:54.334 --> 43:57.334
 <I>Well, We Were Always</I>
 <I>Doing The Funnest Things.</I>

43:57.334 --> 44:01.400
We Never Had
A Dull Moment.

44:01.400 --> 44:05.434
 <I>I Thought All Families</I>
 <I>Were Like That.</I>

44:05.434 --> 44:08.200
I Thought Life
Would Be Like That.

44:11.467 --> 44:14.501
- Here We Are.
- I Don't Like The Dark Meat

44:14.501 --> 44:15.934
Touching The Light.

44:15.934 --> 44:17.868
Of Course Not.

44:17.868 --> 44:19.734
 <I>Did I Mention, Lois,</I>

44:19.734 --> 44:21.868
That I'll Be Having
A Staged Reading

44:21.868 --> 44:24.501
Of My George Eliot Play
This Winter In Palm Beach?

44:24.501 --> 44:28.367
Vivian Cudlip Has Secured
A Ballroom For Me In The Colony.

44:28.367 --> 44:29.834
Really, Henry?

44:29.834 --> 44:32.868
You're Planning To Be
In Palm Beach This Winter?

44:32.868 --> 44:34.534
Well, Of Course.

44:34.534 --> 44:37.801
And I Was Thinking
That You Would Be Perfect

44:37.801 --> 44:40.067
For The George Eliot Role.
What Do You Say?

44:40.067 --> 44:42.901
If You're Angling To Stay
In My Guest Room, Henry,

44:42.901 --> 44:45.400
I Can't Have You
This Season.

44:45.400 --> 44:48.100
I've Invited Meredith.

44:48.100 --> 44:51.801
I Think The Sun'll
Be Very Good For Her
Bad Knee, Don't You?

44:51.801 --> 44:54.701
- Lagerfeld?
- That's Correct.

44:54.701 --> 44:55.834
Meredith.

44:58.133 --> 44:59.834
( BANGING PLATE )

45:03.234 --> 45:06.467
This Roasted Chicken
Is Delicious.

45:09.367 --> 45:13.100
Henry, I Was Wondering
If You're Free Tomorrow.

45:13.100 --> 45:17.467
I Found An Inexpensive
Sports Doctor

45:17.467 --> 45:21.067
For My Knee 
In Brooklyn.

45:21.067 --> 45:23.167
( LAUGHING )

45:26.534 --> 45:29.767
I Was Wondering
If You Might Drive Me
To My Appointment?

45:29.767 --> 45:32.501
Find Someone Else.
I'm Teaching Tomorrow.

45:34.501 --> 45:36.334
I Don't Think
I Can Make It To
The Whitney Later Either.

45:36.334 --> 45:38.968
Every Exhibit Is The Same--

45:38.968 --> 45:41.167
Toilet Seats
And Sex Organs.

45:41.167 --> 45:44.601
I'm No Longer In The Mood
For That Sort Of Thing.

45:44.601 --> 45:48.601
Louis, We're Leaving.

45:48.601 --> 45:49.734
Now!

45:54.734 --> 45:57.534
I'm Sorry Things
Didn't Work Out Tonight.

45:59.200 --> 46:00.667
Right.

46:04.100 --> 46:06.000
( SIGHS HEAVILY )

46:06.000 --> 46:09.801
Thank You For Taking Me.
I Had A Very Nice Time
At The Gallery.

46:09.801 --> 46:11.267
The Whole Damned Evening

46:11.267 --> 46:12.901
Was Engineered
By Lagerfeld

46:12.901 --> 46:16.601
To Get Me To Drive Her
And Her Fat Knees
To Brooklyn.

46:16.601 --> 46:18.567
Of Course She's Not Going
To Ask Lois.

46:18.567 --> 46:21.000
She Wouldn't Do Anything
To Jeopardize That Room,

46:21.000 --> 46:23.367
Now That She's Got Her Grubby
Little Paws On It.

46:23.367 --> 46:25.200
Don't Dwell On It, Henry.

46:25.200 --> 46:27.467
Lets Try To Focus

46:27.467 --> 46:30.267
 <I>On Something Positive</I>
 <I>Like You Tell Me.</I>

46:30.267 --> 46:32.167
Yes. Yes.

46:32.167 --> 46:34.133
Yes, I Suppose
You're Right.

46:34.133 --> 46:36.133
Yes.

46:36.133 --> 46:38.534
That Roasted Chicken
Was Good.

46:38.534 --> 46:40.133
I'll Try To Focus
On That.

46:43.501 --> 46:44.934
 <I>( ENGINE SQUEAKING,</I>
 <I>CREAKING )</I>

46:46.968 --> 46:50.767
Now What In God's Name
Is Happening?

46:52.901 --> 46:55.567
Let's Look Under
The Hood! Out!

46:58.334 --> 47:01.767
No No No No No
No No No.

47:01.767 --> 47:03.534
Not My Car!

47:06.300 --> 47:09.734
No No.
Not My Electra.

47:09.734 --> 47:12.634
If I Lose That,
I Lose Everything.

47:12.634 --> 47:15.901
Let's Just Leave
It Here Tonight.

47:15.901 --> 47:17.334
We'll Come Back
In The Morning,

47:17.334 --> 47:18.767
Get It Towed
And Repaired.

47:18.767 --> 47:20.400
Really?
With What Money?

47:20.400 --> 47:22.734
We'll Figure
Something Out.

47:22.734 --> 47:25.234
Let's Just
Get A Taxi Home.

47:25.234 --> 47:26.801
No.

47:26.801 --> 47:29.968
No, You Go.
I Can't Now.

47:29.968 --> 47:32.801
I Need To Walk
This Whole Evening Off.

47:32.801 --> 47:34.501
Oh, Come On, Henry.

47:34.501 --> 47:36.934
You Shouldn't Do
Such A Long Walk Alone.

47:36.934 --> 47:39.367
What Do I Look Like?!
A Feeble Old Man?

47:39.367 --> 47:41.534
You've Been In Manhattan
For 10 Minutes,

47:41.534 --> 47:43.334
You're Going To Tell Me
What To Do?

47:43.334 --> 47:45.300
I Told You I Want
To Walk Home Alone.

47:45.300 --> 47:46.968
- I Was Just--
- I--

47:46.968 --> 47:50.067
Just Go!
I Don't Need You.

47:52.734 --> 47:55.701
 <I>( CLASSICAL</I>
 <I>MUSIC PLAYING )</I>

48:04.567 --> 48:07.200
No Dancing Today,
Huh, Henry?

48:11.400 --> 48:13.267
Hmm.

48:16.934 --> 48:18.868
 <I>( FOOTSTEPS</I>
 <I>APPROACHING )</I>

48:18.868 --> 48:20.300
Louis?

48:20.300 --> 48:22.100
I'm Sorry, Were You
Reading Something?

48:22.100 --> 48:23.834
I Didn't Mean
To Interrupt You.

48:23.834 --> 48:27.033
No. No.
No, I Was Just--

48:29.467 --> 48:30.801
No, I Wasn't
Reading Anything.

48:30.801 --> 48:34.267
I Realize We Never Went Out
And Had That Lunch.

48:34.267 --> 48:36.100
Are You By Chance
Available Today?

48:40.434 --> 48:42.534
 <I>Did I Mention A Few</I>
 <I>Of Us From Work</I>

48:42.534 --> 48:45.467
Are Going To See "I Am Cuba"
At The Cinema Village Tonight?

48:45.467 --> 48:47.133
You Should Come.

48:47.133 --> 48:48.400
Really?

48:49.734 --> 48:52.167
That Would Be Wonderful.
Thank You.

48:54.801 --> 48:56.767
I Find You Funny, Louis.

48:56.767 --> 48:58.200
In What Way?

48:58.200 --> 49:01.968
I Mean,
You're Interesting.

49:01.968 --> 49:04.901
Sometimes You Remind Me
Of A Guy From Another
Time Period--

49:04.901 --> 49:07.767
Like The '20S.

49:07.767 --> 49:10.100
It's Funny
You Should Say That.

49:10.100 --> 49:12.267
I Love That Era--

49:12.267 --> 49:13.968
The Literature
From That Era.

49:13.968 --> 49:16.300
I Never Told Anyone This,

49:16.300 --> 49:19.067
But Sometimes,
In My Head,

49:19.067 --> 49:20.968
I Actually Imagine

49:20.968 --> 49:23.334
There's Somebody
Narrating My Life,

49:23.334 --> 49:27.100
( WHISPERING )
As If I'm The Protagonist
In A Classic Novel.

49:29.267 --> 49:30.434
Okay.

49:30.434 --> 49:31.901
Narrator:
 <I>The Young Gentleman</I>

49:31.901 --> 49:34.300
 <I>Immediately Regretted</I>
 <I>This Confession.</I>

49:34.300 --> 49:37.133
 <I>He Struggled To Quickly</I>
 <I>Change The Subject.</I>

49:37.133 --> 49:39.033
So I Never Asked You,

49:39.033 --> 49:40.901
How Did The Whole
Upstate Thing Go?

49:40.901 --> 49:42.968
Amazing.

49:42.968 --> 49:44.801
You Should Come
To The Next One.

49:44.801 --> 49:47.534
And Bring Someone Of Course.
Do You Live Alone?

49:47.534 --> 49:50.367
No, I Have A Roommate,
But He's Much Older.

49:50.367 --> 49:52.234
Old, Actually.

49:52.234 --> 49:54.200
I Just Rent A Room
In His Apartment.

49:54.200 --> 49:56.467
To Be Honest,
It's Not Going So Well.

49:56.467 --> 49:59.133
He Gets Irrationally
Mad At Me.

50:00.467 --> 50:02.701
Maybe He's
In Love With You.

50:02.701 --> 50:04.000
No.

50:04.000 --> 50:05.901
No.

50:05.901 --> 50:08.501
I Would Never Want
To Think Of Him Like That.

50:08.501 --> 50:11.501
There Was One Time
It Crossed My Mind But--

50:11.501 --> 50:14.567
Why? What Did He Do
That Made You Wonder?

50:14.567 --> 50:16.868
Well,

50:16.868 --> 50:18.701
It's Kind Of Strange,

50:18.701 --> 50:20.901
But We Were
Drinking Wine

50:20.901 --> 50:22.868
And I Was Lying
On The Floor

50:22.868 --> 50:25.868
Trying To Work Up
The Energy To Go To Bed,

50:25.868 --> 50:28.601
And Something
Very Odd Happened.

50:47.534 --> 50:48.901
That's It?

50:48.901 --> 50:51.567
( LAUGHS )

50:51.567 --> 50:53.868
I Guess It Was Nothing.

50:53.868 --> 50:56.334
I Don't Know Why
I Just Told You That.

50:56.334 --> 50:58.601
I'm Sorry.

50:58.601 --> 51:03.100
Louis, There's Something
I Wanted To Ask You.

51:03.100 --> 51:05.367
Sure.

51:05.367 --> 51:08.634
Well, You Know That Guy
I Started Seeing?

51:08.634 --> 51:10.567
He's Going To Jamaica
On Thursday,

51:10.567 --> 51:12.567
And He Invited Me
To Come With Him.

51:12.567 --> 51:14.467
I Really
Really Wanna Go.

51:14.467 --> 51:16.701
I've Never Been Out
Of The Country Before,

51:16.701 --> 51:18.467
And I'm So
Into Bob Marley.

51:18.467 --> 51:20.868
But George Is Giving Me
A Hard Time At Work

51:20.868 --> 51:22.567
With All The Photo
Clearances Piling Up,

51:22.567 --> 51:25.634
So I Convinced Him
That You Could Cover For Me

51:25.634 --> 51:26.767
While I Was Away.

51:26.767 --> 51:28.901
It's Just
For A Couple Days.

51:34.501 --> 51:37.934
Sure.
Whatever You Need.

51:40.067 --> 51:44.033
You Are The Best.
I Owe You A Major Favor!

51:44.033 --> 51:45.167
( SHRIEKS )

51:45.167 --> 51:46.400
 <I>( CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING )</I>

51:46.400 --> 51:48.334
Henry:
 <I>Ow Ow Ow.</I>

51:48.334 --> 51:50.567
 <I>Ow Ow Ow.</I>

51:51.634 --> 51:54.067
Ow. Oh, Hello!

51:56.300 --> 52:00.334
- How Are You?
- I'm All Right.

52:00.334 --> 52:02.367
You Certainly
Seem Better. 

52:02.367 --> 52:04.400
Yes, My Funk
Has Lifted,

52:04.400 --> 52:07.100
Although I Couldn't
Tell You Why.

52:07.100 --> 52:09.200
I Got A Call
From The Gas Station.

52:09.200 --> 52:11.400
They Said Just To Get
My Car To Run

52:11.400 --> 52:13.200
 <I>Will Cost</I>
 <I>A Small Fortune.</I>

52:13.200 --> 52:14.701
I Did, However, Hear

52:14.701 --> 52:16.801
About A Very Promising
Room In Palm Beach.

52:18.567 --> 52:20.534
- Good For You.
- <I>Which Reminds Me--</I>

52:20.534 --> 52:23.334
I Have A Proposal

52:23.334 --> 52:25.367
Which Might
Save You Money.

52:25.367 --> 52:29.534
What If You Were
To Let Me Borrow Your Car

52:29.534 --> 52:32.367
To Keep With Me
In Florida,

52:32.367 --> 52:33.534
Just For Two Months- 

52:33.534 --> 52:34.834
In Exchange For

52:34.834 --> 52:37.567
My Paying
Your Auto Insurance

52:37.567 --> 52:39.000
 <I>During That Time.</I>

52:39.000 --> 52:41.801
So That's Your Motivation
For Speaking To Me Again?

52:41.801 --> 52:45.767
Well--
Partially, Yes.

52:45.767 --> 52:48.634
It's An Idea I Thought
Would Benefit Us Both.

52:48.634 --> 52:51.367
Why Don't You Follow
Through On Your Offer

52:51.367 --> 52:53.767
To Introduce Me
To Vivian Cudlip's Niece?

52:53.767 --> 52:56.267
That Would Be Of
A Lot More Use To Me

52:56.267 --> 52:57.467
Right Now
Than Insurance Money.

52:59.534 --> 53:02.367
No, I Can't.
It Wouldn't Be Right.

53:03.968 --> 53:05.100
Why?

53:06.667 --> 53:08.334
Is Something
So Wrong With Me?

53:08.334 --> 53:09.734
( SIGHS )

53:12.567 --> 53:14.033
Uh, It's--

53:14.033 --> 53:16.567
I Can't Lend You My Car.

53:16.567 --> 53:19.367
It Has Special Meaning.
My Father Left It To Me.

53:21.868 --> 53:24.067
 <I>I Didn't Mean</I>
 <I>To Upset You.</I>

53:24.067 --> 53:26.734
Let's Just Sweep

53:26.734 --> 53:28.734
The Whole Suggestion
Under The Carpet.

53:28.734 --> 53:30.934
- <I>Hmm?</I>
- <I>( PHONE RINGING )</I>

53:30.934 --> 53:32.200
Excuse Me.

53:34.801 --> 53:36.534
H. Harrison.

53:36.534 --> 53:39.467
Why, Gershon,
What A Surprise.

53:40.567 --> 53:41.834
 <I>My Car?</I>

53:41.834 --> 53:43.267
 <I>Yes, It Did.</I>

53:44.501 --> 53:46.067
 <I>You Will?</I>

53:46.067 --> 53:48.667
 <I>Uh, I--</I>
 <I>I'll Be Right Down.</I>

53:50.634 --> 53:52.968
 <I>* Antiques </I>

53:52.968 --> 53:55.534
 <I>* Every Other Sentiment</I>
 <I>An Antique *</I>

53:56.901 --> 54:00.467
 <I>* As Obsolete As Warships</I>
 <I>In The Baltic *</I>

54:00.467 --> 54:03.267
 <I>* When I'm Driving *</I>

54:03.267 --> 54:06.601
- <I>* I'm On A Straight Road,</I>
 <I> It Never Alters... *</I>
- Hello.

54:06.601 --> 54:10.567
 <I>* And The Radio Serenades</I>
 <I>But Doesn't Falter... *</I>

54:10.567 --> 54:12.167
- Come On!
- Come Back Here!

54:12.167 --> 54:15.334
 <I>* You Offer Infrared</I>
 <I>Instead Of Sun *</I>

54:16.801 --> 54:20.467
 <I>* You Offer Paper Spoons</I>
 <I>And Bubble Gum *</I>

54:24.200 --> 54:25.634
Ma--

54:25.634 --> 54:28.734
 <I>* ...4:00 In The Morning </I>

54:28.734 --> 54:31.067
Mary! Mary!

54:31.067 --> 54:33.100
Louis?

54:36.400 --> 54:38.033
What Are You Doing Here?

54:38.033 --> 54:40.567
I'm Sorry I Couldn't
Make The Movie.

54:40.567 --> 54:42.100
But I Was
In The Neighborhood,

54:42.100 --> 54:44.234
And Thought You Might
Need A Ride Home.

54:44.234 --> 54:46.534
Oh. Well,

54:46.534 --> 54:49.634
I'm Pretty Religious
About Public Transportation.

54:49.634 --> 54:53.467
You Don't Actually Drive
This Thing Around The City,
Do You?

54:53.467 --> 54:55.734
No No.
Of Course Not.

54:55.734 --> 54:59.234
I Was Helping Out
My Friend Lagerfeld.

54:59.234 --> 55:03.067
She's Quite Enormous,
And Has Trouble Getting Around.

55:03.067 --> 55:05.267
Oh.

55:05.267 --> 55:07.167
That's Really
Nice Of You.

55:07.167 --> 55:09.534
Well, Since You're
Already Out And About.

55:13.501 --> 55:15.167
Buckle Up.

55:18.200 --> 55:22.300
Now I Owe You Two Favors.
I'm Not Sure I Can
Handle All This.

55:22.300 --> 55:24.100
No, You Don't
Owe Me Anything.

55:24.100 --> 55:25.734
Oh, Go Straight.
Go Straight.

55:25.734 --> 55:28.834
This Is Brad's Block.
I'm Staying There Tonight.

55:28.834 --> 55:30.634
Oh.

55:30.634 --> 55:33.434
What's That?

55:33.434 --> 55:36.567
"Sally's. New York's
Hottest Tranny Bar"?

55:36.567 --> 55:39.000
People Are Always Leaving
Stupid Stuff In My Car.

55:39.000 --> 55:41.033
- Just Throw It Out.
- Hey Hey, Littering?

55:41.033 --> 55:42.701
- ( SCREAMING )
- <I>( TIRES SQUEALING )</I>

55:42.701 --> 55:45.467
- A Lion!
- Oh My God!

55:45.467 --> 55:46.834
( LAUGHING )

55:49.033 --> 55:52.367
- Mary: <I>Oh My God.</I>
- I'm Sorry.

55:52.367 --> 55:54.767
I Seriously Just Had
A Heart Attack.

55:54.767 --> 55:58.200
I'm Just Having

55:58.200 --> 56:02.267
The Worst Day Ever, Mary.

56:02.267 --> 56:03.968
Let's Go See
What That Was.

56:05.601 --> 56:07.100
- Shit.
- Go Go Go.

56:07.100 --> 56:10.300
Oh, God.
Did I Kill It?

56:13.834 --> 56:16.400
Somebody's Idea
Of A Joke.

56:16.400 --> 56:18.267
 <I>He Is Kind</I>
 <I>Of Cute, Though.</I>

56:18.267 --> 56:21.100
- ( LAUGHS ) He Is.
- You Know What, Louis?

56:21.100 --> 56:23.334
I Think I'm Just...

56:23.334 --> 56:25.667
Going To Walk The Rest
Of The Way From Here.

56:25.667 --> 56:27.901
- Oh, Sure.
- <I>Bye, You Two!</I>

56:31.501 --> 56:34.601
Okay Okay Okay.

56:36.467 --> 56:39.334
( GROANING )
Oh God.

56:40.968 --> 56:42.634
Henry:
 <I>We'll Speak</I>
 <I>In The Morning, Gershon.</I>

56:42.634 --> 56:45.601
Get Some Rest.
You're Looking More
Haggard Than Usual.

56:47.667 --> 56:49.367
Oh God!

56:49.367 --> 56:53.501
You Should Really Stop
Lurking About In The Shadows,

56:53.501 --> 56:55.601
 <I>It's Becoming A Serious</I>
 <I>Character Flaw.</I>

56:55.601 --> 56:58.734
I Just Got In.
Excuse Me.

56:58.734 --> 57:02.000
What A Disastrous Evening.

57:02.000 --> 57:04.467
My God, Gershon Served

57:04.467 --> 57:06.901
Boiled Tongue For Dinner.

57:06.901 --> 57:10.133
 <I>And Then Later We Taxied Over</I>
 <I>To Take A Look At My Car,</I>

57:10.133 --> 57:13.767
And Gershon Confirmed That
It's Completely Beyond Repair.

57:13.767 --> 57:17.000
However, I Did Remember
That The Last Time

57:17.000 --> 57:18.901
I Was Out At Vivian's Place
In Southampton

57:18.901 --> 57:22.133
I Happened To Notice
A Beautiful Vehicle For Sale

57:22.133 --> 57:24.701
 <I>Out By The Bay,</I>
 <I>Where The Riff Raff Stay.</I>

57:24.701 --> 57:28.501
Gershon And I Were Thinking
Of Going Up This Weekend--

57:28.501 --> 57:30.534
Have A Look,
See If It's Still There.

57:30.534 --> 57:32.501
Want To Come Along?

57:32.501 --> 57:36.334
I Take It You're
Just Looking For A Ride?

57:36.334 --> 57:37.801
Yes,

57:37.801 --> 57:40.934
But Why Focus On It
That Way?

57:40.934 --> 57:42.534
Think Of Yourself!

57:42.534 --> 57:45.968
It's Supposed
To Be An Unseasonably
Beautiful Weekend,

57:45.968 --> 57:47.734
Courtesy
Of Global Warming.

57:47.734 --> 57:50.334
And I Think You'd Enjoy
Meeting Gershon.

57:50.334 --> 57:53.701
He's-- Well, Different.

57:56.033 --> 57:57.767
( HONKING )

58:03.434 --> 58:05.033
Where's Gershon?

58:05.033 --> 58:07.400
Gershon Is
Pathologically Late.

58:07.400 --> 58:10.234
Why Don't You Go In
And Urge Him On?

58:11.501 --> 58:12.934
I Don't Even Know Him.

58:12.934 --> 58:14.901
You Really Should See
His Apartment.

58:14.901 --> 58:16.300
It's Quite Interesting.

58:18.267 --> 58:19.501
Okay.

58:19.501 --> 58:22.167
I'll Just Take It
For A Little Spin.

58:22.167 --> 58:23.300
Joking.

58:24.367 --> 58:26.334
 <I>Oh, Look.</I>

58:26.334 --> 58:28.701
( SPEAKING French )
 <I>Decapotable.</I>

58:28.701 --> 58:31.000
( LAUGHS )

58:39.901 --> 58:41.400
Gershon?

58:47.200 --> 58:48.234
Gershon?

58:50.100 --> 58:52.801
( KNOCKS )
Gershon?

58:53.868 --> 58:56.133
 <I>Hello?</I>

59:03.734 --> 59:06.334
Oh! Hello, I'm Louis--

59:06.334 --> 59:08.868
Henry's Roommate.

59:08.868 --> 59:11.300
We Were Waiting
In The Car

59:11.300 --> 59:12.801
And Henry Wanted Me To--

59:12.801 --> 59:14.667
( HIGH VOICE )
Please Accept My Apologies.

59:16.400 --> 59:18.601
I Was Just Putting
My Shoes On.

59:18.601 --> 59:20.634
No, Of Course.

59:28.367 --> 59:30.701
Wow, Look At This.

59:30.701 --> 59:33.234
You Have So Many
Interesting Things.

59:33.234 --> 59:35.701
( HIGH VOICE CONTINUING )
Yes, I Collect Souvenirs.

59:35.701 --> 59:38.234
Must Have Been Everywhere.

59:38.234 --> 59:39.501
No.

59:39.501 --> 59:40.934
I Actually Have
Never Been Anywhere.

59:40.934 --> 59:43.100
Too Busy Working.

59:43.100 --> 59:46.634
What Kind Of Work
Do You Do, Gershon?

59:46.634 --> 59:48.767
I'm A Subway Mechanic.

59:53.200 --> 59:54.834
- Sorry.
- Anyway...

59:54.834 --> 59:57.667
I Do Love My Job.,

59:58.901 --> 01:00:00.567
But It's Always
Been My Dream

01:00:00.567 --> 01:00:01.634
To Buy A Sailboat

01:00:01.634 --> 01:00:03.767
And Sail Off
With A Beautiful Woman

01:00:03.767 --> 01:00:05.200
To The Mediterranean.

01:00:05.200 --> 01:00:07.067
We'd Travel Straight
To The Blue Grotto,

01:00:07.067 --> 01:00:09.367
Where Tiny Rowboats Wait.

01:00:09.367 --> 01:00:13.367
Then We'd Paddle Out
Into The Warm Wet Cave,

01:00:13.367 --> 01:00:15.934
And Kiss And Sing

01:00:15.934 --> 01:00:19.167
And Harmonize
With Our Own Echoes.

01:00:21.234 --> 01:00:22.934
I Still Believe
It's Possible.

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:25.667
The Boat And The Woman.

01:00:27.667 --> 01:00:30.701
 <I>( Henry SINGING</I>
 <I>IN French )</I>

01:00:36.367 --> 01:00:38.367
What's That Song?
That's A Good One.

01:00:38.367 --> 01:00:41.033
From An Operetta I Saw
When I Was Living In Paris--

01:00:41.033 --> 01:00:43.734
 <I>"Pas Sur La Bouche."</I>
"Not On The Mouth."

01:00:43.734 --> 01:00:45.901
It's About A Man
Who Doesn't Like

01:00:45.901 --> 01:00:47.300
To Be Kissed
On The Mouth.

01:00:47.300 --> 01:00:48.667
That's The Whole Plot.

01:00:48.667 --> 01:00:51.267
- No, That's Insane!
- <I>Why? I Happen To Agree.</I>

01:00:51.267 --> 01:00:53.501
Rubbing Noses Is
Far More Sanitary.

01:00:53.501 --> 01:00:56.000
How Did You Afford
To Live Abroad, Henry?

01:00:56.000 --> 01:00:58.067
I Had An Inheritance.

01:00:58.067 --> 01:01:00.734
 <I>Both My Parents Were Dead</I>
 <I>By The Time I Was 22.</I>

01:01:00.734 --> 01:01:02.968
So I Moved To Europe
For 10 Years,

01:01:02.968 --> 01:01:05.467
Spent Every Last Cent.

01:01:05.467 --> 01:01:07.834
Did Both Your Parents
Die At The Same Time?

01:01:07.834 --> 01:01:10.501
My Father Died 
When I Was Two.

01:01:10.501 --> 01:01:13.234
Actually I Was Raised
By My Bohemian Aunt. 

01:01:13.234 --> 01:01:14.534
Why Not Your Mother?

01:01:14.534 --> 01:01:19.200
My Mother Was Afraid Of Me.
My Aunt Understood Me.

01:01:19.200 --> 01:01:21.434
She Taught Literature
At Johns Hopkins.

01:01:21.434 --> 01:01:24.901
She Was Always
Taking Ships To Europe

01:01:24.901 --> 01:01:27.601
And Having Love Affairs.

01:01:27.601 --> 01:01:31.434
Quite Beautiful,
But She Never Married.

01:01:31.434 --> 01:01:33.434
 <I>Fascinating Woman.</I>

01:01:33.434 --> 01:01:35.033
Sounds Like You
Really Loved Her.

01:01:37.968 --> 01:01:40.100
This Is Starting To Sound
Like An Interview.

01:01:40.100 --> 01:01:42.200
Are You Planning To Write
The Unauthorized Biography

01:01:42.200 --> 01:01:45.467
Of An Obscure Playwright
Whose Masterpiece Was Stolen
By A Hunchback?

01:01:45.467 --> 01:01:48.300
Is It So Wrong
To Be Interested In You?

01:01:48.300 --> 01:01:50.033
Yes!
I'm Not Interested In You.

01:01:50.033 --> 01:01:52.133
From Now On
I Intend To Give You

01:01:52.133 --> 01:01:53.968
The Most Misleading
Image Possible.

01:01:53.968 --> 01:01:56.200
You May Write
My Biography,

01:01:56.200 --> 01:01:58.267
But You Will Never
Capture My Soul.

01:02:06.801 --> 01:02:08.734
Henry:
Thank God
We've Finally Landed.

01:02:08.734 --> 01:02:11.133
Between Manhattan
And The East End,

01:02:11.133 --> 01:02:13.834
There's Nothing
But Cemeteries And Strip Clubs.

01:02:13.834 --> 01:02:17.634
Did You Know
That Topless Bars

01:02:17.634 --> 01:02:19.667
Do Their Best Business
On Mother's Day?

01:02:19.667 --> 01:02:21.434
 <I>It's The Udders.</I>

01:02:21.434 --> 01:02:24.167
That's The Day Men
Most Need To See Them.

01:02:24.167 --> 01:02:26.133
That Actually Makes
Lots Of Sense.

01:02:26.133 --> 01:02:29.400
This Certainly
Is A Beautiful Inlet.

01:02:29.400 --> 01:02:31.133
 <I>Maybe It's A Cove.</I>

01:02:31.133 --> 01:02:33.934
I Believe The Appropriate Word
Is Actually "Bight."

01:02:33.934 --> 01:02:36.467
 <I>B-I-G-H-T,</I>

01:02:36.467 --> 01:02:40.868
A Noun Meaning
"A Wide Bay Formed
By Curved Land."

01:02:40.868 --> 01:02:44.334
 <I>There's All Kinds</I>
 <I>Of Wonderful Words</I>
 <I>In The Bs Actually.</I>

01:02:44.334 --> 01:02:47.200
My Personal Favorite
Is "Bisextile,"

01:02:47.200 --> 01:02:49.033
 <I>Which Means Nothing</I>
 <I>Like It Sounds.</I>

01:02:49.033 --> 01:02:50.534
Believe It Or Not
It Means,

01:02:50.534 --> 01:02:52.968
"Of Or Pertaining
To Leap Year."

01:02:52.968 --> 01:02:55.834
So Next February 29th,

01:02:55.834 --> 01:02:57.033
We Should All Remember

01:02:57.033 --> 01:02:59.767
To Wish Each Other
A Happy Bisextile Day!

01:02:59.767 --> 01:03:01.167
( LAUGHING )

01:03:07.000 --> 01:03:09.400
Thank God
It's Still Here.

01:03:10.667 --> 01:03:12.968
Look At Her.
Oh, Yes.

01:03:12.968 --> 01:03:17.434
- A Thing Of Beauty.
- The 1975 Cadillac
V-8 El Dorado.

01:03:17.434 --> 01:03:20.434
- Henry: <I>Excellent.</I>
- 400 Horsepower,

01:03:20.434 --> 01:03:24.000
- 500 Pound-Feet Of Torque...
- Mm-Hmm.

01:03:24.000 --> 01:03:25.801
...And Single Digit
Gas Mileage.

01:03:25.801 --> 01:03:27.901
That's Terrible
For The Environment.

01:03:27.901 --> 01:03:29.634
Oh, And I Suppose
Yours Is Better?

01:03:29.634 --> 01:03:32.667
It Seems The Owners Have
Left For The Season.

01:03:32.667 --> 01:03:35.434
 <I>We Should Call And Arrange</I>
 <I>A Test Drive, Henry.</I>

01:03:35.434 --> 01:03:36.567
We've Come All This Way,

01:03:36.567 --> 01:03:38.801
We Might As Well Have
A Peek Under The Hood.

01:03:38.801 --> 01:03:40.734
Climb In There
And Try And Open Her Up.

01:03:40.734 --> 01:03:44.067
It's Open.

01:03:44.067 --> 01:03:46.067
New Tires.
That's Good.

01:03:46.067 --> 01:03:48.767
Okay.
Henry, I Can't--

01:03:48.767 --> 01:03:51.567
 <I>Let Gershon Do It.</I>
 <I>He's The Mechanically</I>
 <I>Inclined One.</I>

01:03:51.567 --> 01:03:53.300
I Don't See One.

01:03:53.300 --> 01:03:55.701
Maybe This Is
A Secret Hood Release.

01:03:55.701 --> 01:03:57.300
- Oh, No!
- No!

01:03:58.534 --> 01:04:00.167
Scheisse.

01:04:01.968 --> 01:04:04.200
 <I>Better Vamoose Before</I>
 <I>The</I> Polizei <I>Arrive.</I>

01:04:04.200 --> 01:04:08.934
- Louis: <I>Henry.</I>
- Woman: <I>Who's That?</I>

01:04:08.934 --> 01:04:11.968
Henry:
At Least I Have
A Piece Of A New Car.

01:04:11.968 --> 01:04:13.267
Tomorrow I'll Call
And Inquire

01:04:13.267 --> 01:04:15.434
As To The Price
Of The Rest Of It.

01:04:15.434 --> 01:04:16.601
Louis:
Henry, You Can't.

01:04:16.601 --> 01:04:18.801
That's Like Returning
To The Scene Of A Crime.

01:04:18.801 --> 01:04:20.868
Are You Insane?
They'd Never Suspect Me.

01:04:20.868 --> 01:04:22.234
Who'd Be Stupid Enough

01:04:22.234 --> 01:04:25.167
To Deface A Car And Then
Inquire About Its Price?

01:04:25.167 --> 01:04:26.634
You Know, Gershon,

01:04:26.634 --> 01:04:28.601
This Young Man
Is Very Well Read,

01:04:28.601 --> 01:04:30.868
But He Knows Nothing
About Real Life.

01:04:30.868 --> 01:04:33.267
Yes, I'm Starting
To Think That.

01:04:33.267 --> 01:04:36.701
Yes, He's Such A Sad,
Old Soul Too.

01:04:36.701 --> 01:04:40.200
You Know That He's Never
Even Learned How To Dance?

01:04:40.200 --> 01:04:42.934
That's More Than Sad.
That's Tragic.

01:04:42.934 --> 01:04:46.400
Well, If Henry Would Let Me
Watch Him Once In A While,

01:04:46.400 --> 01:04:48.434
I Might Pick Up
A Step Or Two.

01:04:48.434 --> 01:04:50.000
My Steps Cannot
Be Learned.

01:04:50.000 --> 01:04:53.834
They're Entirely Intuitive,
Based On Jungle Rhythms.

01:04:53.834 --> 01:04:54.801
Try Me.

01:04:56.334 --> 01:04:58.667
( CHUCKLES )
Very Well.

01:05:00.467 --> 01:05:02.834
Gershon, You've Got
A Beautiful Singing Voice.

01:05:02.834 --> 01:05:06.067
We Hear You In The Shower
All The Time, Going On And On.

01:05:06.067 --> 01:05:08.467
Why Don't You Sing Us
Something That's Danceable?

01:05:08.467 --> 01:05:10.300
What Genre Do You Prefer?

01:05:10.300 --> 01:05:12.100
Um...
I Don't Know.

01:05:12.100 --> 01:05:13.667
Let's Start
With A Waltz.

01:05:14.734 --> 01:05:16.834
- ( CLEARS THROAT )
- Yeah.

01:05:16.834 --> 01:05:18.801
Over Here.
We Need Space.

01:05:18.801 --> 01:05:24.133
- Now Observe And Imitate.
- ( DEEP VOICE )
* Somewhere My Love... 

01:05:24.133 --> 01:05:27.167
- Oh, Yes.
- * There Will Be
Songs To Sing... *

01:05:27.167 --> 01:05:29.701
So Once He's Singing,
He Has A Human Voice.

01:05:29.701 --> 01:05:32.501
Now Shoulders So.
Chest Out.

01:05:32.501 --> 01:05:36.200
Aristocratic.
Watch Closely.
Do As I Do.

01:05:36.200 --> 01:05:40.100
- One, Two, Three,
 One, Two, Three.
- <I>* Somewhere A Hill... </I>

01:05:40.100 --> 01:05:44.267
- That's Right. Yes. Float!
- <I>* Blossoms In Green</I>
 <I> And Gold *</I>

01:05:44.267 --> 01:05:48.601
- * And There Are Dreams... 
- <I>Don't Bend Your Knees</I>
 <I> Too Much.</I>

01:05:48.601 --> 01:05:51.467
It's Not A Peasant Dance.
You're An Aristocrat!

01:05:51.467 --> 01:05:52.734
You're Above The World.

01:05:52.734 --> 01:05:56.133
- * Someday... 
- You're Floating.

01:05:56.133 --> 01:05:59.000
- <I>* We'll Meet Again... *</I>
- One And Turn, And Turn.

01:05:59.000 --> 01:06:01.767
- <I>* My Love... </I>
- Whirl-- The Dervishes!

01:06:01.767 --> 01:06:07.801
- It's Transcendent.
- * Someday, Whenever
The Spring Breaks Through. *

01:06:07.801 --> 01:06:10.501
That's It. Yes!
Ohh! Oh, Oh!

01:06:10.501 --> 01:06:12.801
- Henry! Henry, Are You Okay?
- ( Henry GROANING, SHOUTING )

01:06:12.801 --> 01:06:14.534
- Are You Okay?
- My Sciatica!

01:06:14.534 --> 01:06:16.467
What Do We Do?!

01:06:16.467 --> 01:06:19.234
What Do You Do?
Get Me Off This
Godforsaken Beach.

01:06:19.234 --> 01:06:21.634
I Need Alcohol
And Civilization.

01:06:21.634 --> 01:06:23.367
- Okay. Okay.
- Oh, God.

01:06:23.367 --> 01:06:25.467
( GROANING )

01:06:25.467 --> 01:06:28.200
- Oh, God. Oh, God.
- How Do We Do This?

01:06:28.200 --> 01:06:31.801
( GROANING )
Don't Forget My Hat!

01:06:31.801 --> 01:06:33.901
Vivian Cudlip Bought
That For Me In Moscow!

01:06:33.901 --> 01:06:35.701
( HIGH VOICE )
Put Him On The Floor.

01:06:35.701 --> 01:06:38.434
I Know How To Fix Him.
I Did It Two Years Ago.

01:06:38.434 --> 01:06:39.934
No, You Didn't.
You Made It Worse.

01:06:39.934 --> 01:06:41.901
 <I>Don't Be Difficult,</I>
 <I>Henry.</I>

01:06:41.901 --> 01:06:45.100
I'm The One Who Got You
Walking Again And You Know It.

01:06:45.100 --> 01:06:46.234
It's A Conspiracy,
Isn't It?

01:06:46.234 --> 01:06:47.634
Otto Bellman Hired You,
Didn't He?

01:06:47.634 --> 01:06:49.567
- To Assassinate Me.
- <I>Kneel Down.</I>

01:06:49.567 --> 01:06:52.133
Tell Him He Can Keep
My Damn Play!

01:06:52.133 --> 01:06:54.200
- <I>On Your Stomach.</I>
 <I> All Right.</I>
- ( GROANING )

01:06:54.200 --> 01:06:56.033
Shh. Now...

01:06:56.033 --> 01:06:58.667
I'm Going To Begin
By Applying Sharp Pressure...

01:06:58.667 --> 01:06:59.734
( SPITS )

01:06:59.734 --> 01:07:03.000
To The Areas Just Above
Both Buttocks.

01:07:03.000 --> 01:07:04.767
What?
Not With Your Hands
You're Not!

01:07:04.767 --> 01:07:08.234
I Don't Want Your Germs.
Use Some Other Technique.

01:07:08.234 --> 01:07:09.934
Fine.

01:07:12.767 --> 01:07:14.133
Here, I'll Use This.

01:07:14.133 --> 01:07:16.267
Oh, I Don't Know About That,
Gershon. It Doesn't Look--

01:07:16.267 --> 01:07:18.501
- I'll Make It Work.
- What? What Are You--

01:07:18.501 --> 01:07:21.734
- Hold Still.
- ( SCREAMING )

01:07:22.801 --> 01:07:24.634
Are You Insane?!
God!

01:07:24.634 --> 01:07:26.767
You're Trying To Kill Me!

01:07:26.767 --> 01:07:29.400
How In God's Name Is
That Supposed To Help?!

01:07:29.400 --> 01:07:32.234
- Hey, Here's Some Brandy.
- I Know.

01:07:32.234 --> 01:07:34.100
I Need To Go Get
My Acupressure Book.

01:07:34.100 --> 01:07:36.634
And I Have A Very Large
Vibrator Downstairs.

01:07:36.634 --> 01:07:38.400
- Mmm.
- I'll Be Right Back.

01:07:40.467 --> 01:07:41.934
Oh, God.

01:07:41.934 --> 01:07:44.901
Louis, I Think I See My--
My Eye Mask.

01:07:44.901 --> 01:07:47.667
It's My Eye Mask,
Isn't It?

01:07:47.667 --> 01:07:49.334
Oh My... God.

01:07:49.334 --> 01:07:50.868
Ohh!

01:07:50.868 --> 01:07:53.601
Mmm! Oh.

01:07:54.901 --> 01:07:57.167
Let Me Get You A Pillow.

01:07:57.167 --> 01:07:58.300
Louis. Louis.

01:07:58.300 --> 01:08:00.000
For God's Sake,
Do Not--

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:04.000
Do Not Let...
Gershon In With His Vibrator.

01:08:04.000 --> 01:08:05.701
You Can Imagine Where
That Thing's Been.

01:08:05.701 --> 01:08:07.734
All I Need Is Sleep.

01:08:07.734 --> 01:08:10.267
I Need To Put On
My Eye Mask.

01:08:10.267 --> 01:08:12.367
Don't Worry.
I'll Handle Gershon.

01:08:15.834 --> 01:08:18.834
If, By Chance,
I Die In My Sleep,

01:08:18.834 --> 01:08:20.501
I Want You To Make Sure

01:08:20.501 --> 01:08:23.300
That The Funeral Mass
Is In <I>Latin.</I>

01:08:23.300 --> 01:08:26.600
And Give All My Worldly Goods
To Catholic Charities,

01:08:26.600 --> 01:08:29.334
Except For The Christmas Balls.
Those Go To You.

01:08:29.334 --> 01:08:32.200
You're Not Going To Die.
Just Get Some Sleep, Okay?

01:08:32.200 --> 01:08:35.133
Yes, Sleep.

01:08:35.133 --> 01:08:37.133
You Know, Louis,

01:08:37.133 --> 01:08:39.367
In Spite
Of Your Quirks,

01:08:39.367 --> 01:08:41.901
 <I>I Think You're</I>
 <I>The Sanest Person I Know.</I>

01:08:41.901 --> 01:08:44.901
I'm Very Lucky
To Have You Here.

01:08:46.701 --> 01:08:48.667
- <I>( DOOR BANGS )</I>
- Gershon: <I>I've Got</I>
 <I> The Vibrator!</I>

01:08:48.667 --> 01:08:49.600
( SCREAMS )

01:08:53.466 --> 01:08:56.300
 <I>( PHONE RINGING )</I>

01:08:58.300 --> 01:08:59.300
( GROANS )

01:08:59.300 --> 01:09:00.600
I Got It.

01:09:02.133 --> 01:09:03.466
I Got It.

01:09:07.300 --> 01:09:10.100
H. Harrison's Residence.

01:09:10.100 --> 01:09:12.667
Oh. Yes.

01:09:12.667 --> 01:09:14.667
Just One Minute,
Please.

01:09:14.667 --> 01:09:17.801
It's Vivian Cudlip's
Secretary.

01:09:22.868 --> 01:09:25.000
H. Harrison.

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:26.300
 <I>I'm Sorry?</I>

01:09:27.701 --> 01:09:30.901
Oh. Oh, Vivian,
How Are You, Dear?

01:09:32.000 --> 01:09:36.133
Yes. Oh,
That Sounds Lovely.

01:09:36.133 --> 01:09:38.901
Yes, I Look Forward To It.

01:09:40.600 --> 01:09:43.033
Oh, God, God, God, God.

01:09:43.033 --> 01:09:44.567
Is Something Wrong?

01:09:44.567 --> 01:09:47.399
Vivian's Hosting
A Dinner Party Tonight
At The Russian Tea Room.

01:09:47.399 --> 01:09:48.968
She Wants Me
To Escort Her.

01:09:48.968 --> 01:09:51.868
And Look At Me, Lying Here
Like A Useless Old Man.

01:09:51.868 --> 01:09:54.367
Maybe You Should
Just Call Her Back

01:09:54.367 --> 01:09:56.100
 <I>And Tell Her</I>
 <I>The Truth.</I>

01:09:56.100 --> 01:09:57.334
I'm Sure
She'd Understand.

01:09:57.334 --> 01:09:59.934
At Her Age She Must
Have Health Problems.

01:09:59.934 --> 01:10:03.100
Vivian Has Had Every Cancer
There Is-- Twice.

01:10:03.100 --> 01:10:05.667
Not To Mention A Hole
In Her Heart.

01:10:05.667 --> 01:10:07.868
But That Hasn't Stopped Her
Ever From Going Out.

01:10:09.367 --> 01:10:12.267
If I Let Vivian Contact
Any Of The Other Rosen Knights,

01:10:12.267 --> 01:10:13.767
 <I>I'll Be Banished.</I>

01:10:13.767 --> 01:10:16.067
But, Henry,
There's No Way You Can Go.

01:10:16.067 --> 01:10:18.100
No.

01:10:18.100 --> 01:10:20.000
No.

01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:21.534
But You Can.

01:10:23.601 --> 01:10:24.567
Me?

01:10:43.534 --> 01:10:45.167
 <I>( DOORBELL RINGS )</I>

01:10:47.501 --> 01:10:50.267
Hello. I'm Here
For Mrs. Cudlip.

01:10:50.267 --> 01:10:51.901
Woman:
 <I>Come In.</I>

01:10:57.033 --> 01:10:58.334
Wait Here.

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:03.300
( WHISPERING )

01:11:03.300 --> 01:11:04.801
Come In.

01:11:10.234 --> 01:11:11.667
 <I>You're Louis.</I>

01:11:11.667 --> 01:11:13.734
Henry's Young Friend.

01:11:13.734 --> 01:11:15.000
 <I>Yes.</I>

01:11:15.000 --> 01:11:18.801
It's A Pleasure
To Meet You, Mrs. Cudlip.

01:11:18.801 --> 01:11:21.067
I've Heard Nothing
But Wonderful Things.

01:11:21.067 --> 01:11:23.734
Well, If Henry Said Them,
Don't Believe A Word.

01:11:23.734 --> 01:11:27.234
Lately That Man Is
Not To Be Trusted.

01:11:28.801 --> 01:11:31.767
He Introduced
My Granddaughter

01:11:31.767 --> 01:11:34.901
To A Deformed
Swiss Con Man,

01:11:34.901 --> 01:11:36.601
And I'm Not Happy
About It.

01:11:36.601 --> 01:11:40.434
- That's Shocking.
- He Can Be A Dear
Friend, Henry,

01:11:40.434 --> 01:11:44.534
But He's Annoyingly Intent
At Being Something More.

01:11:44.534 --> 01:11:48.701
He's Always Dropping Hints
About Marrying Me, You Know.

01:11:48.701 --> 01:11:50.334
No, I Didn't.

01:11:50.334 --> 01:11:53.634
And My Other Friend, Aresh,
Is The Same Way.

01:11:53.634 --> 01:11:56.801
( CHUCKLING )
You'll Meet Him At Dinner.

01:11:56.801 --> 01:12:00.267
- This Rose Is For You.
- Very Thoughtful.

01:12:01.767 --> 01:12:03.868
The Car's Waiting.

01:12:03.868 --> 01:12:06.200
- May I Help You?
- Let's Go.

01:12:07.434 --> 01:12:09.100
Get This For You.

01:12:12.534 --> 01:12:16.334
So What Do You Think
Of The Russian Tea Room, Louis?

01:12:16.334 --> 01:12:20.000
This Caviar Is Wonderful.
The Champagne As Well.

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:21.467
Yes. I Want More.

01:12:21.467 --> 01:12:25.133
Right Away, Mrs. Cudlip.
Anything You Need, Just Ask.

01:12:27.200 --> 01:12:29.767
( SPEAKING Arabic )

01:12:29.767 --> 01:12:31.834
A Toast To Vivian.

01:12:31.834 --> 01:12:35.501
- Oh, Yes.
- The Most Beautiful,

01:12:35.501 --> 01:12:37.801
The Most Sophisticated,
The Most Cultured...

01:12:37.801 --> 01:12:40.467
- Waiter, I Need A Straw.
- <I>...The Most Prominent...</I>

01:12:40.467 --> 01:12:43.367
- Of Course.
- ...And The Most Popular

01:12:43.367 --> 01:12:47.000
Grand Dame
In All Of New York!

01:12:47.000 --> 01:12:48.167
( SUCKING )

01:12:49.801 --> 01:12:52.367
Also, You Have Received
A Phone Message, Mrs. Cudlip.

01:12:52.367 --> 01:12:53.334
Oh, Thank You.

01:12:55.334 --> 01:12:57.701
It's Nice To See
You Again, Meredith.

01:12:57.701 --> 01:13:01.167
Oh.

01:13:01.167 --> 01:13:02.534
Oh, That's Right. Yes.

01:13:02.534 --> 01:13:03.801
Yes, Hello.

01:13:03.801 --> 01:13:06.167
I'm Sorry We Couldn't
Accompany You And Lois

01:13:06.167 --> 01:13:07.834
To The Whitney
That Night.

01:13:07.834 --> 01:13:09.801
Henry Was A Bit
Out Of Sorts.

01:13:09.801 --> 01:13:11.300
You Mean Rude.

01:13:11.300 --> 01:13:13.133
But You Know,
I Don't Care.

01:13:13.133 --> 01:13:15.100
Henry Is Horrible
To All Women.

01:13:15.100 --> 01:13:17.367
Oh, I Don't Think
That's True.

01:13:17.367 --> 01:13:19.667
He Had His Heart
Broken Years Ago

01:13:19.667 --> 01:13:21.501
When He Was Young
And Handsome

01:13:21.501 --> 01:13:22.901
And Still Had Money,

01:13:22.901 --> 01:13:25.934
And He Takes It Out
On Women Ever Since.

01:13:25.934 --> 01:13:29.000
 <I>You Know, He Was In Love</I>
 <I>With A Catholic Girl.</I>

01:13:29.000 --> 01:13:31.067
Her Family Wouldn't
Accept Him.

01:13:31.067 --> 01:13:33.334
 <I>Henry's Protestant,</I>

01:13:33.334 --> 01:13:36.734
And He Pretends
Ever Since To Be Catholic

01:13:36.734 --> 01:13:40.267
Because He Thinks It Has Some
Sort Of Moral Snob Appeal.

01:13:40.267 --> 01:13:43.300
Spencer Mooney
Told Me He Suspects

01:13:43.300 --> 01:13:46.234
That Henry
Is Homosexual.

01:13:46.234 --> 01:13:47.701
People Say That Too.

01:13:47.701 --> 01:13:49.601
 <I>And He Was</I>
 <I>In The Theater.</I>

01:13:49.601 --> 01:13:51.801
Theater Types Need To Be
A Little Homosexual

01:13:51.801 --> 01:13:53.801
So They Can Feel Things
More Deeply.

01:13:53.801 --> 01:13:56.334
But Henry Is The Opposite--
He Has No Feelings.

01:13:56.334 --> 01:13:58.767
- I Don't Think So.
- Oh, I Think So.

01:13:58.767 --> 01:14:00.634
I Give Up.

01:14:00.634 --> 01:14:02.000
Louis,

01:14:02.000 --> 01:14:04.968
Could You Read This Name
Here For Me, Please?

01:14:04.968 --> 01:14:06.968
Of Course.

01:14:06.968 --> 01:14:09.000
"Barry Barbarash."

01:14:09.000 --> 01:14:10.767
Oh, I'm Not Going
To Answer That.

01:14:10.767 --> 01:14:12.634
If He Hears
I'm With Other Men,

01:14:12.634 --> 01:14:15.434
He Just Gets
Wildly Jealous.

01:14:15.434 --> 01:14:18.267
Yes, Vivian, I Wouldn't
Encourage Him.

01:14:18.267 --> 01:14:20.334
He Is Charming

01:14:20.334 --> 01:14:22.667
And Has Very Wonderful
Long Legs,

01:14:22.667 --> 01:14:25.634
But He Spies On You,
Vivian, In Palm Beach.

01:14:25.634 --> 01:14:28.200
Yes.
He Has Binoculars

01:14:28.200 --> 01:14:30.267
And He Looks At You

01:14:30.267 --> 01:14:32.868
When You Undress
In Your Room At The Colony.

01:14:32.868 --> 01:14:34.300
Don't Get Started, Aresh.

01:14:34.300 --> 01:14:36.767
- Just Look At Your Menu...
- Yes.

01:14:36.767 --> 01:14:39.400
...And Pick Out
An Entree Please.

01:14:39.400 --> 01:14:42.767
How About Barbarash's
Head On A Plate?

01:14:42.767 --> 01:14:44.734
( CHUCKLING )

01:14:44.734 --> 01:14:47.767
You See?
You're No Better
Than Any Of Them.

01:14:47.767 --> 01:14:49.634
 <I>You're Just As Jealous.</I>

01:14:49.634 --> 01:14:52.267
Wouldn't You Agree
With Me, Louis?

01:14:52.267 --> 01:14:55.567
Well, Wanting Someone's
Head On A Plate

01:14:55.567 --> 01:14:57.601
With Flaming Cognac

01:14:57.601 --> 01:14:59.667
Does Sound A Little
Jealous To Me.

01:14:59.667 --> 01:15:01.334
What "Flaming Cognac"?

01:15:01.334 --> 01:15:02.501
( LAUGHING )
"Flaming Cognac"!

01:15:02.501 --> 01:15:05.601
- ( ALL LAUGHING )
- Louis, I Like You.

01:15:05.601 --> 01:15:07.901
I Like You So Much.

01:15:07.901 --> 01:15:10.167
( SHOUTING Arabic )

01:15:16.334 --> 01:15:17.400
( LAUGHS NERVOUSLY )

01:15:17.400 --> 01:15:20.267
 <I>I Didn't Mean </I>
 <I>To Offend Him.</I>

01:15:20.267 --> 01:15:21.968
Did I Really Hurt
His Feelings?

01:15:21.968 --> 01:15:24.868
Oh Yes, I Think So.
Aresh Offends Easily.

01:15:24.868 --> 01:15:27.701
I'm Terribly Sorry.

01:15:27.701 --> 01:15:29.467
Please Excuse Me.

01:15:30.534 --> 01:15:32.901
( SUCKING )

01:15:32.901 --> 01:15:34.300
Henry's Protege.

01:15:40.033 --> 01:15:41.534
Aresh.

01:15:41.534 --> 01:15:45.434
She Doesn't Know
How Much She Hurt Me.

01:15:46.634 --> 01:15:49.934
 <I>I've Lost My Country.</I>
 <I>Everything.</I>

01:15:49.934 --> 01:15:52.133
She Could
So Easily Help Me,

01:15:52.133 --> 01:15:54.467
But She Doesn't Even
Consider It.

01:15:56.701 --> 01:15:58.634
I Am Through With Her.

01:16:00.968 --> 01:16:04.234
I Am Through
With Vivian Cudlip.

01:16:10.334 --> 01:16:11.467
Mary:
 <I>Louis?</I>

01:16:13.567 --> 01:16:15.334
Oh My God,
It Is You!

01:16:15.334 --> 01:16:18.300
Brad, This Is
The Guy From "Terra"
I Was Telling You About.

01:16:18.300 --> 01:16:20.267
- <I>The One That</I>
 <I> Covered For Me.</I>
- Hey, Man.

01:16:20.267 --> 01:16:23.000
- <I>Thanks A Million, Really.</I>
- Sure. Sure.

01:16:23.000 --> 01:16:26.234
We Just Got Out
Of "The Women Of World Music"
Show At Carnegie Hall.

01:16:26.234 --> 01:16:28.801
- <I>What Are You Doing Up Here?</I>
- Oh, You Know,

01:16:28.801 --> 01:16:30.534
Just Having
Dinner With Some Friends.

01:16:30.534 --> 01:16:32.534
Here?

01:16:32.534 --> 01:16:35.334
- Yes.
- Oh My God,
That's Perfect.

01:16:35.334 --> 01:16:37.200
Louis!

01:16:37.200 --> 01:16:41.167
Don't You Dare
Let Aresh's Nonsense

01:16:41.167 --> 01:16:43.167
Ruin Our Evening.

01:16:43.167 --> 01:16:46.767
I Never Loved That Iranian
And I Never Will,

01:16:46.767 --> 01:16:49.467
So Get Back In There.

01:16:54.033 --> 01:16:56.834
I Have To Go.
I'll See You At The Office.

01:17:01.567 --> 01:17:04.033
- Come In.
- Champagne.

01:17:12.434 --> 01:17:15.067
Upstairs To The Left.

01:17:15.067 --> 01:17:16.067
Okay.

01:17:16.067 --> 01:17:18.367
I'll Carry You.

01:18:03.868 --> 01:18:05.667
Good Night, Vivian.

01:18:07.634 --> 01:18:10.067
Thank You
For A Spectacular Evening.

01:18:10.067 --> 01:18:13.133
No,

01:18:13.133 --> 01:18:16.634
Thank You, Dear Boy.

01:18:19.534 --> 01:18:21.067
Tonight,

01:18:21.067 --> 01:18:23.000
You Were Nothing Short

01:18:23.000 --> 01:18:26.133
Of A Perfect Gentleman.

01:18:34.968 --> 01:18:37.334
- <I>( DOOR CLOSES )</I>
- Ah, Here We Are.

01:18:38.934 --> 01:18:40.734
Henry, You're Walking.

01:18:40.734 --> 01:18:42.334
 <I>Yes, A Miracle.</I>

01:18:42.334 --> 01:18:45.400
 <I>Gershon's Magic Vibrator</I>
 <I>Got Me Up And Running Again,</I>

01:18:45.400 --> 01:18:47.067
At Least Temporarily.

01:18:47.067 --> 01:18:48.667
How Was Your Evening?

01:18:50.334 --> 01:18:51.701
It Was Wonderful.

01:18:51.701 --> 01:18:53.834
Vivian And I Got Along
Beautifully.

01:18:53.834 --> 01:18:55.701
You Weren't Supposed
To Do That Well.

01:18:55.701 --> 01:18:59.534
I Sent You There
To Keep My Rivals At Bay,
Not To Become One Of Them.

01:18:59.534 --> 01:19:01.834
Actually,
I Feel Sorry For Vivian.

01:19:01.834 --> 01:19:04.501
Everybody Seems To Want
Something From Her,

01:19:04.501 --> 01:19:06.334
And Yet She's
Still So Sweet.

01:19:06.334 --> 01:19:10.267
Sweet? Vivian?
She's A Monster.

01:19:10.267 --> 01:19:12.434
You Should See The Way
She Treats Her Staff.

01:19:12.434 --> 01:19:14.367
It's Like Something
Out Of "Peter The Great."

01:19:14.367 --> 01:19:15.667
Oh.

01:19:15.667 --> 01:19:17.567
Well, Maybe She's
A Sweet Monster.

01:19:17.567 --> 01:19:18.634
Why Are You Packing?

01:19:18.634 --> 01:19:21.067
- I'm Going To Florida.
- Huh? 

01:19:21.067 --> 01:19:22.334
Yes.

01:19:22.334 --> 01:19:23.868
Sun, Vermouth

01:19:23.868 --> 01:19:26.534
And Codeine Is
My Only Hope For A Cure.

01:19:26.534 --> 01:19:28.868
When Are You Leaving?

01:19:28.868 --> 01:19:30.767
Tonight,
On The Midnight Bus.

01:19:37.801 --> 01:19:39.367
( SIGHS )

01:19:40.534 --> 01:19:42.934
So There We Are.
Where Are We?

01:19:42.934 --> 01:19:45.834
I'm Going
To Miss You, Henry.

01:19:45.834 --> 01:19:47.434
Don't Be Ridiculous.

01:19:47.434 --> 01:19:48.767
But I Am.

01:19:48.767 --> 01:19:52.100
 <I>Can I At Least Help You</I>
 <I>With Your Bag?</I>

01:19:52.100 --> 01:19:55.501
They Make Them
With Wheels Now.
I'll Manage.

01:19:55.501 --> 01:19:58.033
So Try Not To Burn Down
The Apartment,

01:19:58.033 --> 01:20:00.300
 <I>And No Guests.</I>

01:20:00.300 --> 01:20:02.667
You Know The Rules.
I'll See You In The Spring!

01:20:10.901 --> 01:20:12.634
( HORN HONKING )

01:20:30.834 --> 01:20:35.300
 <I>* Sunday Morning </I>

01:20:35.300 --> 01:20:40.234
 <I>* Brings The Dawn In </I>

01:20:40.234 --> 01:20:43.601
 <I>* It's Just</I>
 <I>A Restless Feeling *</I>

01:20:44.667 --> 01:20:47.934
 <I>* By My Side </I>

01:20:49.000 --> 01:20:52.434
 <I>* Early Dawning </I>

01:20:53.701 --> 01:20:58.200
 <I>* Sunday Morning </I>

01:20:58.200 --> 01:21:05.667
 <I>* It's Just The Wasted Years</I>
 <I>So Close Behind *</I>

01:21:06.734 --> 01:21:08.167
 <I>* Watch Out </I>

01:21:08.167 --> 01:21:10.934
 <I>* The World's Behind You *</I>

01:21:10.934 --> 01:21:14.868
 <I>* There's Always Someone</I>
 <I>Around You *</I>

01:21:14.868 --> 01:21:18.567
 <I>* Who Will Call </I>

01:21:18.567 --> 01:21:22.334
 <I>* It's Nothing At All *</I>

01:21:43.133 --> 01:21:47.601
 <I>* Watch Out,</I>
 <I>The World's Behind You *</I>

01:21:47.601 --> 01:21:51.167
 <I>* There's Always Someone</I>
 <I>Around You *</I>

01:21:51.167 --> 01:21:54.400
 <I>* Who Will Call </I>

01:21:54.400 --> 01:21:58.601
 <I>* It's Nothing At All *</I>

01:22:01.200 --> 01:22:05.167
 <I>* Sunday Morning </I>

01:22:06.267 --> 01:22:10.100
 <I>* Sunday Morning. </I>

01:22:10.100 --> 01:22:12.667
 <I>( DOOR OPENING )</I>

01:22:12.667 --> 01:22:14.167
Hen-- Henry?

01:22:18.934 --> 01:22:20.367
 <I>( KEYS JINGLING )</I>

01:22:29.400 --> 01:22:31.567
( GASPS )

01:22:33.300 --> 01:22:34.534
I'm Otto Bellman.

01:22:34.534 --> 01:22:36.167
I Lived Here Once
With Henry.

01:22:36.167 --> 01:22:37.834
He's In Palm Beach, Yes?

01:22:37.834 --> 01:22:40.200
Oh. Yes, He Is.

01:22:44.334 --> 01:22:46.200
I Would Like My Mail.

01:22:47.534 --> 01:22:49.901
Okay.
Please, Come In.

01:22:51.300 --> 01:22:53.601
And Excuse My Appearance.

01:22:57.033 --> 01:22:59.467
I Don't Forget
This Place.

01:22:59.467 --> 01:23:01.934
It Is Most Filthy Home
I Ever Lived In.

01:23:12.934 --> 01:23:14.534
Why Is It So Cold?

01:23:14.534 --> 01:23:16.501
Henry Kept It
In The Freezer.

01:23:19.567 --> 01:23:22.400
( LAUGHS )

01:23:22.400 --> 01:23:24.567
Oh, Henry.

01:23:24.567 --> 01:23:26.200
( LAUGHING )

01:23:27.501 --> 01:23:31.267
 <I>Henry Is Very Original,</I>
 <I>Don't You Think?</I>

01:23:31.267 --> 01:23:34.701
Christmas Balls,
Very Original.

01:23:34.701 --> 01:23:37.734
Dancing, Very Original.

01:23:37.734 --> 01:23:40.767
Sneaking Into The Opera,
Very Original.

01:23:40.767 --> 01:23:43.167
He And I Went
Six Times Together.

01:23:45.434 --> 01:23:46.467
That Many?

01:23:46.467 --> 01:23:49.367
What Is Your Name?

01:23:49.367 --> 01:23:51.100
Oh, I'm Sorry. Louis.

01:23:51.100 --> 01:23:52.300
Louis?

01:23:52.300 --> 01:23:56.100
- Ah, Louis Ives.
- Yes.

01:23:56.100 --> 01:23:59.300
You Are On Vivian's List
To Attend My Wedding.

01:23:59.300 --> 01:24:01.834
I Will Marry
Her Granddaughter, You Know.

01:24:01.834 --> 01:24:05.234
I've Heard.
Congratulations.

01:24:05.234 --> 01:24:07.667
I'm Flattered To Hear
I Made Vivian's List.

01:24:07.667 --> 01:24:09.234
I Would Like Henry
To Attend.

01:24:09.234 --> 01:24:11.601
 <I>He Is Still Mad</I>
 <I>At Me Though.</I>

01:24:11.601 --> 01:24:15.701
He Accuses Me
Of Stealing His Play.

01:24:17.634 --> 01:24:19.200
Anyway,

01:24:19.200 --> 01:24:22.067
I Will Track Him Down
Myself In Palm Beach 

01:24:22.067 --> 01:24:23.501
And Convince Him.

01:24:23.501 --> 01:24:25.434
So The Wedding
Will Be Soon?

01:24:25.434 --> 01:24:26.734
Yes.

01:24:28.567 --> 01:24:30.300
Thank You For Mail.

01:24:30.300 --> 01:24:32.734
I Go See Gershon Now.

01:24:42.634 --> 01:24:44.367
Mary:
 <I>Brad Is Always Complaining</I>

01:24:44.367 --> 01:24:46.701
About The Ratty T-Shirts
I Sleep In.

01:24:46.701 --> 01:24:48.501
Oh No.

01:24:48.501 --> 01:24:52.300
- <I>Oh My God.</I>
- The Sales Girl Said
It Would Look Great.

01:24:52.300 --> 01:24:53.534
Oh Yeah!

01:24:53.534 --> 01:24:54.634
- <I>Yeah.</I>
- He's Gonna--

01:24:54.634 --> 01:24:56.200
Shit, Louis!

01:24:56.200 --> 01:24:58.467
- How Embarrassing.
- Don't Worry.

01:24:58.467 --> 01:25:00.767
I Have The Same One.

01:25:00.767 --> 01:25:03.467
( LAUGHING )

01:25:03.467 --> 01:25:07.100
Mary, Could I Talk
To You For A Second

01:25:07.100 --> 01:25:08.634
- Before You Leave?
- Sure.

01:25:08.634 --> 01:25:11.300
I'll Wait For You
In The Hallway.

01:25:16.167 --> 01:25:19.968
So Remember At Lunch

01:25:19.968 --> 01:25:22.367
How You Said You Owe Me
A Big Favor?

01:25:22.367 --> 01:25:24.534
- Mm-Hmm.
- Well,

01:25:24.534 --> 01:25:26.801
As It Turns Out

01:25:26.801 --> 01:25:30.801
I Have Been Invited
To A Society Wedding.

01:25:31.868 --> 01:25:33.400
I'd Like
To Bring A Date,

01:25:33.400 --> 01:25:37.968
But I Don't Really Know
Anyone My Age In Town,

01:25:37.968 --> 01:25:40.200
So I Was Wondering

01:25:40.200 --> 01:25:43.100
If Maybe You'd
Accompany Me.

01:25:43.100 --> 01:25:45.167
Um...

01:25:47.167 --> 01:25:49.367
I'm Pretty Serious
With Brad Right Now,

01:25:49.367 --> 01:25:52.834
- So This Is--
- I Didn't Mean It That Way.

01:25:52.834 --> 01:25:55.734
I Understand You're
In A Relationship.

01:25:55.734 --> 01:25:57.634
 <I>I Just Thought Maybe</I>

01:25:57.634 --> 01:25:59.133
 <I>We Could Go</I>
 <I>As Friends.</I>

01:25:59.133 --> 01:26:01.434
In Fact, I'm Supposed
To Get Introduced

01:26:01.434 --> 01:26:02.868
To A Young Woman There.

01:26:02.868 --> 01:26:06.968
The Niece Of The Bride's
Grandmother.

01:26:06.968 --> 01:26:08.334
I Really Just--

01:26:08.334 --> 01:26:10.467
I Don't Think This Is
The Best Idea.

01:26:11.534 --> 01:26:13.567
Please Don't Be Mad.

01:26:14.734 --> 01:26:17.701
I Just Think That Honesty
Is Super Important,

01:26:17.701 --> 01:26:19.467
And The Truth Is...

01:26:19.467 --> 01:26:21.701
It Makes Me
Uncomfortable.

01:26:21.701 --> 01:26:23.667
Okay.

01:26:23.667 --> 01:26:25.234
I Understand.

01:26:26.934 --> 01:26:28.901
Have A Great Weekend.

01:26:28.901 --> 01:26:30.901
 <I>I'll See You Monday.</I>

01:26:51.300 --> 01:26:53.167
 <I>( DANCE MUSIC PLAYING )</I>

01:26:55.701 --> 01:26:57.767
I Adore You.

01:26:59.033 --> 01:27:00.868
 <I>Hey, Baby.</I>

01:27:04.267 --> 01:27:06.400
Can I Get You
Anything Else, Honey?

01:27:06.400 --> 01:27:08.167
No, Thank You.
I'm Fine.

01:27:08.167 --> 01:27:09.434
Okay.

01:27:21.100 --> 01:27:23.133
Is This Your
First Time Here?

01:27:25.868 --> 01:27:27.934
Yes, Actually It Is.

01:27:30.033 --> 01:27:32.601
I'm Miss Pepper,
And If You're Interested

01:27:32.601 --> 01:27:35.200
In Dating A Woman
Like Me, You Can.

01:27:35.200 --> 01:27:38.534
Many Of The Beautiful Girls
Here Are Available
For A Date.

01:27:38.534 --> 01:27:41.033
For A Donation, That Is.

01:27:41.033 --> 01:27:43.100
I Don't Think So,

01:27:45.133 --> 01:27:47.634
But They Are
Beautiful.

01:27:49.167 --> 01:27:51.734
I Don't Understand
How You Do It.

01:27:52.868 --> 01:27:54.934
Oh.

01:27:57.834 --> 01:27:59.267
You Know,

01:27:59.267 --> 01:28:01.133
You'd Actually Make
A Pretty Girl Yourself.

01:28:01.133 --> 01:28:05.167
Put On A Fierce Blond Wig
To Go With Your Bright Eyes.

01:28:05.167 --> 01:28:07.200
 <I>Contour Your Nose A Bit.</I>

01:28:07.200 --> 01:28:10.167
My Nose Is Very Masculine,
Isn't It?

01:28:10.167 --> 01:28:12.167
Honey, If There's
A Woman In There,

01:28:12.167 --> 01:28:14.801
It Would Take More
Than A Nose To Keep Her Down.

01:28:31.501 --> 01:28:32.868
George?

01:28:32.868 --> 01:28:34.701
Yes.

01:28:34.701 --> 01:28:36.667
You Must Be Sandra.
Please Come In.

01:28:36.667 --> 01:28:38.467
Where Do You
Want To Do This?

01:28:38.467 --> 01:28:40.501
I Usually Suggest
The Kitchen.

01:28:40.501 --> 01:28:42.267
Okay. Sure.

01:28:42.267 --> 01:28:43.801
Great. Strip Down
To Your Underwear

01:28:43.801 --> 01:28:45.334
And We'll Get Started.

01:28:49.767 --> 01:28:51.868
This Is What
I'd Like To Wear.

01:28:53.801 --> 01:28:55.901
Sure, If It Fits.

01:28:57.534 --> 01:28:59.434
You Given Any Thought
To The Wig?

01:28:59.434 --> 01:29:00.934
I Brought Three.

01:29:00.934 --> 01:29:03.434
Yes. I'd Like
Brunette, Please.

01:29:03.434 --> 01:29:05.901
In Fact,

01:29:05.901 --> 01:29:08.033
I Would Like To Look...

01:29:09.167 --> 01:29:11.367
As Much As Possible
Like Her.

01:29:18.667 --> 01:29:22.367
* A Plume Of Doom
Will Rise *

01:29:23.968 --> 01:29:29.400
* Eluding Hearts
And Skies *

01:29:29.400 --> 01:29:34.133
* Destroying Eagles' Eyes *

01:29:34.133 --> 01:29:37.234
* While We All Lament 

01:29:37.234 --> 01:29:42.801
* This Business
Of Cement. *

01:29:42.801 --> 01:29:43.767
 <I>What Was That?</I>

01:29:46.033 --> 01:29:48.200
I Thought Maybe I Would
Contribute A Song

01:29:48.200 --> 01:29:49.367
To The Next Rally.

01:29:49.367 --> 01:29:51.300
 <I>I Think It Kind </I>
 <I>Of Works, Maybe.</I>

01:29:51.300 --> 01:29:53.601
- ( HISSES )
- What?

01:29:53.601 --> 01:29:54.868
It's A Little
Corny, No?

01:29:54.868 --> 01:29:56.701
Oh.

01:29:56.701 --> 01:29:58.467
- It's Not Finished Yet.
- ( CHUCKLES )

01:29:59.934 --> 01:30:01.667
That's Not Very Nice.

01:30:01.667 --> 01:30:03.334
 <I>Okay. I'm Sorry.</I>
 <I>I Just--</I>

01:30:03.334 --> 01:30:05.701
I Just Believe
That Honesty

01:30:05.701 --> 01:30:07.567
Is Super Important.

01:30:09.300 --> 01:30:10.701
You Know What?
Come On.

01:30:10.701 --> 01:30:12.434
 <I>Let's Go To Bed.</I>

01:30:12.434 --> 01:30:14.467
I'm Dying To See
That Surprise You Got.

01:30:28.334 --> 01:30:29.968
Ready?

01:30:40.334 --> 01:30:41.501
Well?

01:30:43.334 --> 01:30:46.334
Narrator:
 <I>The Young Gentleman's</I>
 <I>Heart Sank.</I>

01:30:46.334 --> 01:30:49.434
 <I>He Looked Nothing Like</I>
 <I>What He Had Imagined. </I>

01:30:49.434 --> 01:30:51.000
 <I>In Fact,</I>

01:30:51.000 --> 01:30:53.801
 <I>He Was Horrified</I>
 <I>By What He Saw.</I>

01:30:53.801 --> 01:30:56.801
Wait Wait.
I Forgot The Jewelry.

01:30:56.801 --> 01:30:58.968
 <I>But With This Crushing</I>
 <I>Disappointment</I>

01:30:58.968 --> 01:31:01.267
 <I>Came A Great</I>
 <I>Revelation--</I>

01:31:01.267 --> 01:31:04.934
 <I>Despite His Occasional</I>
 <I>Penchant For Women's Clothing,</I>

01:31:04.934 --> 01:31:09.234
 <I>Louis Ives Did Not Want</I>
 <I>To Transform Himself.</I>

01:31:09.234 --> 01:31:12.534
 <I>There Was No Woman</I>
 <I>Inside Him Dying To Get Out.</I>

01:31:12.534 --> 01:31:15.968
 <I>He Did Not Long</I>
 <I>To Be Beautiful Like Mary,</I>

01:31:15.968 --> 01:31:18.100
 <I>Or The Girls</I>
 <I>At Sally's. </I>

01:31:18.100 --> 01:31:21.000
 <I>This Was Not</I>
 <I>His Path To Love.</I>

01:31:23.434 --> 01:31:25.200
This Is Wrong.

01:31:25.200 --> 01:31:27.434
- It's All Wrong.
- No!

01:31:27.434 --> 01:31:31.067
No. No, You Look
Really Nice!

01:31:31.067 --> 01:31:35.901
 <I>In Fact, Standing There</I>
 <I>Dressed As A Woman,</I>

01:31:35.901 --> 01:31:38.934
 <I>He Never Felt More</I>
 <I>Like A Man In His Life.</I>

01:31:40.000 --> 01:31:41.300
What?

01:31:41.300 --> 01:31:43.300
What The Hell
Are You Doing?!

01:31:44.834 --> 01:31:47.133
I'm Sorry.
I Didn't Think
I Needed To Ask

01:31:47.133 --> 01:31:48.267
If I Was Paying!

01:31:48.267 --> 01:31:50.467
- What?!
- <I>Please, Stop Yelling.</I>

01:31:50.467 --> 01:31:51.868
- <I>You, Asshole!</I>
- What?

01:31:51.868 --> 01:31:54.601
- I Just Didn't Under--
- <I>What Is Happening Here?</I>

01:31:54.601 --> 01:31:55.968
Henry!

01:31:57.601 --> 01:31:59.801
What--
What Have You Done?

01:32:01.133 --> 01:32:03.968
- Get Out Of My Home!
- What's Going On?!

01:32:03.968 --> 01:32:05.234
- Go, Go!
- Shit!

01:32:05.234 --> 01:32:07.667
- Get Out Of My Home!
- <I>( Sandra SCREAMS )</I>

01:32:07.667 --> 01:32:09.934
- Get Out Of My Home!
- Sandra: <I>Freaks!</I>

01:32:09.934 --> 01:32:11.567
- Go. Go.
- Fucking Freaks!

01:32:11.567 --> 01:32:14.701
- Get Out!
- <I>Jesus Christ!</I>

01:32:14.701 --> 01:32:16.601
I Trusted You.

01:32:16.601 --> 01:32:18.868
I Trusted You.
I Trusted You.

01:32:18.868 --> 01:32:20.467
- Henry--
- <I>Here With Everything</I>
 <I> I Own.</I>

01:32:20.467 --> 01:32:23.000
Henry, I Didn't Know You
Were Coming Home So Soon.

01:32:24.400 --> 01:32:25.767
 <I>I Had To.</I>

01:32:26.834 --> 01:32:29.000
Vivian Died.

01:32:29.000 --> 01:32:31.467
Oh My...

01:32:31.467 --> 01:32:32.734
 <I>God.</I>

01:32:32.734 --> 01:32:34.701
Henry, I'm Sorry.
I'm So Sorry.

01:32:34.701 --> 01:32:36.601
I Don't Want
Your Sympathy.

01:32:36.601 --> 01:32:38.701
- I Only Want Your Absence.
- <I>Henry, Please.</I>

01:32:40.834 --> 01:32:42.667
I'm Going For A Walk.

01:32:42.667 --> 01:32:46.400
I Want You
Out Of My Apartment
By The Time I Get Back.

01:32:46.400 --> 01:32:48.467
Please Wait.
Can't You Just
For Once--

01:32:48.467 --> 01:32:49.501
Henry!

01:32:49.501 --> 01:32:51.767
Henry, I Don't Know
What To Say!

01:32:51.767 --> 01:32:55.000
Look, Obviously
I Have Some Issues!

01:32:55.000 --> 01:32:56.634
Mmm.

01:32:56.634 --> 01:32:58.634
I Tried My Best
To Hide Them,

01:32:58.634 --> 01:33:02.200
Because I Desperately
Wanted Your Friendship.

01:33:03.601 --> 01:33:05.534
But The Real Truth Is

01:33:05.534 --> 01:33:08.601
 <I>I Don't Even</I>
 <I>Know Who You Are.</I>

01:33:08.601 --> 01:33:10.000
Nobody Seems To.

01:33:36.300 --> 01:33:38.767
- ( TIRES SQUEAL )
- ( SCREAMS )

01:33:38.767 --> 01:33:40.067
 <I>( CRASHES )</I>

01:33:50.400 --> 01:33:53.300
Narrator:
 <I>As Louis Ives' Vehicle</I>
 <I>Was Hauled Away...</I>

01:33:54.868 --> 01:33:57.701
 <I>So Was His Entire</I>
 <I>Foundation.</I>

01:33:59.467 --> 01:34:02.734
 <I>And For The First Time</I>
 <I>Since He Moved There, </I>

01:34:02.734 --> 01:34:05.100
 <I>Louis Ives Considered</I>

01:34:05.100 --> 01:34:07.968
 <I>Giving Up</I>
 <I>On Manhattan Altogether.</I>

01:34:32.200 --> 01:34:34.067
( DOOR BUZZES )

01:35:03.434 --> 01:35:05.634
( SPEAKING SOFTLY )

01:35:07.801 --> 01:35:09.801
- Morning, Louis.
- Morning, George.

01:35:59.968 --> 01:36:02.133
Farewell, My Vivian.

01:36:08.000 --> 01:36:09.901
I Shall Always Be

01:36:09.901 --> 01:36:13.300
Your Most Devoted
Rosen Knight.

01:36:29.133 --> 01:36:30.767
( KNOCKS,
CLEARS THROAT )

01:36:30.767 --> 01:36:33.033
You Wanted
To See Me, George?

01:36:33.033 --> 01:36:35.801
Yeah. Yeah, I Did.
Sit Down Please, Louis.

01:36:41.634 --> 01:36:45.200
Is Something...
Wrong?

01:36:45.200 --> 01:36:47.834
There's Just Something
I Need To Talk To You About.

01:36:47.834 --> 01:36:49.501
Okay.

01:36:49.501 --> 01:36:52.434
Louis, Phone Sales,

01:36:52.434 --> 01:36:54.634
They're Not Really
Right For You.

01:36:56.534 --> 01:36:58.434
- No?
- No.

01:36:58.434 --> 01:36:59.601
You're Just--

01:36:59.601 --> 01:37:02.000
You're Not The Right
Personality Type, Louis.

01:37:02.000 --> 01:37:04.334
Now Our Magazine
Is Doing--

01:37:04.334 --> 01:37:06.367
Is Doing Very Well,
You Know That.

01:37:06.367 --> 01:37:08.334
The Editing Staff
Can Barely Keep Up

01:37:08.334 --> 01:37:10.901
With All The Unsolicited
Manuscripts That Are
Coming In.

01:37:10.901 --> 01:37:13.067
So What I Would
Prefer To Do

01:37:13.067 --> 01:37:15.968
Is To Start You
Copy Editing.

01:37:17.167 --> 01:37:19.701
You've Got A Quiet,
Keen Insight, Louis.

01:37:19.701 --> 01:37:21.000
That's An Asset Here.

01:37:21.000 --> 01:37:23.634
We Should Groom You
As A Writer,

01:37:23.634 --> 01:37:25.567
 <I>Not As A Salesman.</I>

01:37:25.567 --> 01:37:27.334
I Guess What
I'm Saying Is,

01:37:27.334 --> 01:37:30.567
I'm Offering You
A Promotion.

01:37:37.267 --> 01:37:38.701
Mary:
 <I>Louis?</I>

01:37:38.701 --> 01:37:40.734
Louis, I Need
To Talk To You.

01:37:40.734 --> 01:37:44.501
I Was Thinking...

01:37:45.734 --> 01:37:48.634
And You Did Me
A Really Selfless Favor,

01:37:48.634 --> 01:37:51.534
And I Was Really Selfish
Not To Return It.

01:37:51.534 --> 01:37:52.601
Oh.

01:37:52.601 --> 01:37:55.200
So If You Still Need
A Date For That Wedding,

01:37:55.200 --> 01:37:57.767
I Would Be Happy

01:37:57.767 --> 01:38:01.067
And Honored
To Fill That Position.

01:38:06.467 --> 01:38:08.234
Mary,

01:38:08.234 --> 01:38:10.634
I Really Appreciate

01:38:10.634 --> 01:38:12.467
You Offering
To Be My Date.

01:38:12.467 --> 01:38:14.300
But I'm Not Sure

01:38:14.300 --> 01:38:17.501
If It's The Best Thing
For Me Anymore.

01:38:18.567 --> 01:38:19.534
Really?

01:38:21.167 --> 01:38:23.934
Are You Throwing Those
Christmas Balls Out?

01:38:45.834 --> 01:38:47.801
 <I>Hello, Henry.</I>

01:38:49.601 --> 01:38:51.434
Look At Them,

01:38:51.434 --> 01:38:54.434
Strutting Around As If
They Own The Whole City...

01:38:55.868 --> 01:38:57.567
And Yet They're
Completely Dependent.

01:38:57.567 --> 01:38:58.901
Not A Pot To Piss In.

01:38:59.968 --> 01:39:03.300
Well, They Do Look
Awfully Proud.

01:39:06.334 --> 01:39:09.133
Henry, I Want To Apologize
For Last Night.

01:39:09.133 --> 01:39:13.367
You Are Always Apologizing.
Don't Be So Obsequious.

01:39:13.367 --> 01:39:15.501
It's Your Apartment.

01:39:15.501 --> 01:39:17.868
They're Your Rules.
I Broke Them.

01:39:17.868 --> 01:39:20.133
Yes...

01:39:20.133 --> 01:39:21.567
All That Is True.

01:39:21.567 --> 01:39:24.133
 <I>But I'm Not</I>
 <I>As Old Fashioned</I>
 <I>As You Think.</I>

01:39:26.467 --> 01:39:31.033
Does That Mean You're
Not Kicking Me Out For Good?

01:39:31.033 --> 01:39:32.567
Don't Be Ridiculous.

01:39:32.567 --> 01:39:35.868
You Did Kick Bellman
Out For Less.

01:39:35.868 --> 01:39:37.133
I Know.

01:39:37.133 --> 01:39:40.601
But There's
A Difference--

01:39:40.601 --> 01:39:42.868
It Would Be Sad
To Lose You.

01:39:51.901 --> 01:39:53.000
Hmm.

01:39:53.000 --> 01:39:55.100
But You Really Do
Need Help, You Know?

01:39:55.100 --> 01:39:56.801
You Might Think
About Going Over

01:39:56.801 --> 01:39:59.033
To The American Legion
For Counseling.

01:39:59.033 --> 01:40:00.267
Hmm.

01:40:00.267 --> 01:40:02.167
No, They'll Get
You Thinking Right.

01:40:02.167 --> 01:40:04.234
Actually, What I've
Decided To Do Is

01:40:04.234 --> 01:40:06.167
To Devote More Time
To Writing--

01:40:06.167 --> 01:40:08.100
Professionally
And Personally.

01:40:08.100 --> 01:40:10.367
I Think It May Be
Therapeutic.

01:40:10.367 --> 01:40:12.167
Good.
Yes, It Helps.

01:40:12.167 --> 01:40:16.133
But I Wouldn't Rule Out
Psychoanalysis Either.

01:40:16.133 --> 01:40:18.200
 <I>I've Thought</I>
 <I>About That Too.</I>

01:40:21.534 --> 01:40:24.000
- Gershon?!
- ( LAUGHS ) Hey!

01:40:24.000 --> 01:40:25.834
You Look Great,
Gershon.

01:40:25.834 --> 01:40:27.767
- Thank You.
- You Look Practically
Middle Class.

01:40:27.767 --> 01:40:30.100
- I Did It
For The Wedding.
- My God.

01:40:34.801 --> 01:40:36.501
What's This?

01:40:45.033 --> 01:40:46.334
My Play!

01:40:47.734 --> 01:40:50.200
Gershon, You?

01:40:50.200 --> 01:40:51.701
I Was Angry.

01:40:51.701 --> 01:40:54.200
And I Was Hurt.

01:40:55.534 --> 01:40:57.567
And I Wanted
To Hurt You Back.

01:40:58.634 --> 01:41:00.400
But I'm Sorry, Henry.

01:41:01.501 --> 01:41:04.567
It Was Wrong.
I Deeply Regret It.

01:41:05.934 --> 01:41:08.901
Can You Find It In Your Heart
To Forgive Me?

01:41:14.868 --> 01:41:17.033
I Forgive You, Gershon.

01:41:17.033 --> 01:41:20.434
You Mustn't Sin Anymore.

01:41:20.434 --> 01:41:22.667
No Sin Against
Your Fellow Man,

01:41:22.667 --> 01:41:24.734
No Sin Against Your Body.

01:41:24.734 --> 01:41:27.734
Follow The Bible.
Work!

01:41:28.868 --> 01:41:31.567
Work On Your Soul.

01:41:31.567 --> 01:41:33.934
Pray For Enlightenment.

01:41:35.234 --> 01:41:37.934
Who Knows, Maybe Louis And I
Will Get Some Too,

01:41:37.934 --> 01:41:39.501
Because We Live
Just Upstairs. 

01:41:40.634 --> 01:41:43.667
And Do You,
Otto Ralph Bellman,

01:41:43.667 --> 01:41:46.901
Take This Woman,
Margaret Chase Cudlip,

01:41:46.901 --> 01:41:48.701
To Be Your Lawfully
Wedded Wife,

01:41:48.701 --> 01:41:51.300
For Richer, For Poorer,

01:41:51.300 --> 01:41:52.934
 <I>In Sickness</I>
 <I>And In Health,</I>

01:41:52.934 --> 01:41:55.133
 <I>So Long As You Both</I>
 <I>Shall Live?</I>

01:41:55.133 --> 01:41:56.634
That's Vivian's Niece.

01:41:56.634 --> 01:41:59.334
- Otto: <I>I Do.</I>
- <I>By The Power Vested In Me</I>

01:41:59.334 --> 01:42:01.033
 <I>By The Almighty God...</I>

01:42:01.033 --> 01:42:03.334
She's A Little Old For Me,
Don't You Think?

01:42:03.334 --> 01:42:05.200
- <I>I Now Pronounce</I>
 <I> You Man And Wife.</I>
- Hmm?

01:42:05.200 --> 01:42:08.767
- She's Barely 50.
- Henry, Shh!

01:42:08.767 --> 01:42:10.334
- Shh!
- Shh!

01:42:10.334 --> 01:42:11.801
- Shh!
- Shh!

01:42:11.801 --> 01:42:13.801
- <I>You May Now Kiss</I>
 <I> The Bride.</I>
- Sacred.

01:42:13.801 --> 01:42:16.467
 <I>( APPLAUSE )</I>

01:42:26.133 --> 01:42:29.868
Congratulations.

01:42:29.868 --> 01:42:32.567
Congratulations, Otto.

01:42:32.567 --> 01:42:33.968
Henry:
I've Been Thinking.

01:42:36.000 --> 01:42:37.534
When I Finish Teaching
In August,

01:42:37.534 --> 01:42:39.701
The Three Of Us
Should Go To Russia.

01:42:39.701 --> 01:42:42.367
Three Can Manage
Very Well There.

01:42:42.367 --> 01:42:44.300
We Won't Need Much.

01:42:44.300 --> 01:42:46.467
A Bottle Of Champagne
Only Costs

01:42:46.467 --> 01:42:49.100
 <I>$4 On The Black Sea.</I>

01:42:49.100 --> 01:42:51.067
Oh, Thank You,
My Dear.

01:42:52.334 --> 01:42:53.534
Lovely.

01:43:00.334 --> 01:43:02.534
 <I>( APPLAUSE )</I>

